(1, 1, 0, 0, 'The Verb \"To Be\"', NULL, 'one', 'The verb [i]to be[/i] describes the identity, qualities, or condition of a person or object.  Use the following to form the present tense of the verb to be:\r\n\r\nI	am	happy.\r\nYou	are	smart.\r\nHe	is	short.\r\nShe	is	busy.\r\nIt	is	tall.\r\nWe	are	tired.\r\nThey	are	here.', NULL, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 05:30:44', '2019-07-13 06:12:30'),
(2, 1, 1, 4, 'The Most Common Verb: \'To Be\'', NULL, 'the-verb--to-be-', 'Introduction to the verb \'To Be\' .', '<p>The verb <strong>To Be</strong>&nbsp;describes the identity, qualities, or condition of a person or object.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Use the following to form the present tense of the verb <strong>To Be:<br /></strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Subject</th>\r\n<th>Verb</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I</td>\r\n<td>am</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>You</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>He, She, It</td>\r\n<td>is</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>We</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>They</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Here are some example sentences using <strong>To Be</strong>:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>I <strong>am</strong> happy.</p>\r\n<p>You <strong>are</strong> smart.</p>\r\n<p>He <strong>is</strong> tall.</p>\r\n<p>She <strong>is</strong> busy.</p>\r\n<p>It <strong>is</strong> purple.</p>\r\n<p>We <strong>are</strong> tired.</p>\r\n<p>They <strong>are</strong> young.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>For regular nouns, the verb form depends on whether the subject is singular (one) or plural (more than one):</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Subject</th>\r\n<th>Verb</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Singular</td>\r\n<td>is</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Plural</td>\r\n<td>are</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>The car <strong>is</strong> red. <strong>&rarr; </strong>Singular, one car</p>\r\n<p>The cars <strong>are</strong> fast. <strong>&rarr; </strong>Plural, more than one car</p>\r\n<p>Here are more examples with singular and plural subjects:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>The tree <strong>is</strong> green.&nbsp; (one tree)</p>\r\n<p>The clouds <strong>are</strong> white.&nbsp; (more than one cloud)</p>\r\n<p>The sky <strong>is</strong> blue.&nbsp; (one sky)</p>\r\n<p>The cows <strong>are</strong> brown.&nbsp; (more than one cow)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-note\">\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> In some languages there is more than one verb for <strong>To Be</strong> but in English there is only one.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Summary</h3>\r\n<p>Most verbs are used for actions but the verb <strong>To Be</strong> describes conditions.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 06:13:24', '2019-07-17 08:35:56'),
(3, 1, 1, 2, 'The Basic Structure', NULL, 'introduction', 'This lesson describes the basic structure of the English language.', '<p>A basic sentence looks like this:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clouds are white.</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clouds</strong> is the <strong>subject</strong>. Subjects are usually nouns. Nouns are people, places, and things.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Are</strong> is the <strong>verb</strong> (the verb is <strong>To Be</strong>) Verbs describe an action or condition.</p>\r\n<p><strong>White</strong> is the <strong>adjective</strong>. Adjective describes the noun.</p>\r\n<p>Here are more examples:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>The sky is blue.</p>\r\n<p>The tree is tall.</p>\r\n<p>The sheep is hungry.</p>\r\n<p>He is young.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Summary</h3>\r\n<p>The word order in a basic sentence is:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Subject/Noun &rarr; Verb &rarr; Adjective</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Nouns</strong> are people, places, and things.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Verbs</strong> are actions or conditions.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Adjectives</strong> describe nouns.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 07:25:36', '2019-07-17 06:38:51'),
(4, 2, 2, 1, 'Frases Avanzadas en Español 1', NULL, 'new-vocabulary', 'El último vocabulario avanzado en español', '<p>Fuera de contacto - ex. Fuera de contacto con la realidad.</p>\r\n<p>Volcado de datos - descarga de datos</p>\r\n<p>Sonado - Emitir [una cosa] alg&uacute;n sonido o ruido.&nbsp; hecho, acontecimiento. Que es muy conocido y tiene mucha repercusi&oacute;n social.</p>\r\n<p>bot&iacute;n - bot&iacute;n pirata</p>\r\n<p>Grieta - El terremoto de California cre&oacute; una grieta gigante en la tierra.</p>\r\n<p>Hedor - Los vecinos avisaron a la Polic&iacute;a de un fuerte hedor que proven&iacute;a de la vivienda.</p>\r\n<p>Paliza - Serie numerosa de golpes dados a una persona como castigo o con la intenci&oacute;n de hacerle da&ntilde;o.</p>\r\n<p>Tarrina - tina; tina de manteca</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 08:05:42', '2019-07-27 20:02:17'),
(5, 1, 1, 3, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', 'To begin, please look up these words in your native language and add them to your vocabulary list.\r\n\r\nThis step requires that you create an account so that your vocabulary list can be saved.  Click here to register your account', NULL, 1, 20, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-13 11:39:16', '2019-08-02 08:57:18'),
