(65, 5, 7, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences using the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong>.&nbsp; Use the information in parenthesis at the end of each sentence to help you determine the correct tense and to know whether the sentence is affirmative or negative.</p>\r\n<p>My daughter (to be) afraid of the dark.&nbsp; (present tense, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>(To be) Jason right?&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>She (to be) hungry for breakfast this morning.&nbsp; (past tense, negative)</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Please open the windows.&nbsp; I (to be) very hot.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I (to be) ashamed of the size of my shoes.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>Cathy (to be) thirty-three years old on her last birthday.&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>We (to be) very thirsty after the race.&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>You (to be) wrong again.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>I (to be) right all the time.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>(To be) you scared of thunder?&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>He (to be) afraid of the lightning.&nbsp; (past, negative)</p>\r\n<p>I (to be) cold this morning.&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>(To be) the guests hungry?&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>My mother and father (to be) ashapmed of my behavior.&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>(To be) your son scared of spiders?&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>I (to be) eighteen years old.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>Bill is happy because (to be) right.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>I (to be) cold because of the snowballs in my pocket.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:01:10', '2020-01-27 21:12:22'),
(66, 5, 7, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>needle</p>\r\n<p>never</p>\r\n<p>crow</p>\r\n<p>shark</p>\r\n<p>jellyfish</p>\r\n<p>frequently</p>\r\n<p>summer</p>\r\n<p>usually</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:11:51', '2019-07-22 00:12:17'),
(67, 5, 7, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences using the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ ashamed of you.&nbsp; (past, negative)</p>\r\n<p>___ they cold at the beach?&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>She ___ right.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>We ___ wrong.&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>Sharon ___ twenty-one years old today.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>It ___ hot last summer.&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>Mark ___ afraid of needles.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>I ___ hungry all the time.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>The baby ___ thirsty.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>He ___ wrong.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___ she right?&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>It ___ cold in Canada in the winter.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___ you scared of sharks?&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___ it hot in your class yesterday?&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___ it cold outside?&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>They ___ wrong.&nbsp; (past, negative)</p>\r\n<p>She ___ ashamed of her son.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>___ you cold?&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>I ___ twenty-two years old.&nbsp; (past, negative)</p>\r\n<p>They ___ ashamed of her.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>Mark ___ right.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___ Ben thirsty?&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>The boys ___ hungry.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>I ___ scared of jellyfish.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>The girls ___ thirsty.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___ they ashamed of me?&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>It ___ afraid of you.&nbsp; (past, negative)</p>\r\n<p>Lucy ___ usually right.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>He ___ scared of crows.&nbsp; (present, negative)</p>\r\n<p>It ___ cold downstairs.&nbsp; (past, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>She ___ frequently wrong.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>___ Peter hungry?&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>\r\n<p>I ___ afraid of the frog.&nbsp; (past, negative)</p>\r\n<p>We ___ very hungry.&nbsp; (present, affirmative)</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:12:31', '2019-07-22 00:22:22'),
(68, 5, 8, 1, 'Adjectives', NULL, 'adjectives', NULL, '<p>Adjectives are used to describe nouns.&nbsp; They are placed before the noun.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>a <strong>little</strong> dog</td>\r\n<td>a <strong>clean</strong> house</td>\r\n<td>a <strong>nice</strong> neighbor</td>\r\n<td>a <strong>good</strong> fried</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>a <strong>pink</strong> flower</td>\r\n<td>a <strong>busy</strong> man</td>\r\n<td>a <strong>good</strong> recipe</td>\r\n<td>a <strong>blue</strong> bucket</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Adjectives never take <strong>-s</strong> even if the noun is plural.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>brown</strong> cows</td>\r\n<td><strong>big</strong> snowflakes</td>\r\n<td><strong>expensive</strong> cars</td>\r\n<td><strong>clean</strong> floors</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>young</strong> girls</td>\r\n<td><strong>pretty</strong> ribbons</td>\r\n<td><strong>dirty</strong> shoes</td>\r\n<td><strong>soft</strong> pillows</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:23:14', '2019-07-25 22:18:27'),
(69, 5, 8, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to drink</p>\r\n<p>to want</p>\r\n<p>to see</p>\r\n<p>to look</p>\r\n<p>hard</p>\r\n<p>little</p>\r\n<p>test</p>\r\n<p>cute</p>\r\n<p>prune</p>\r\n<p>handsome</p>\r\n<p>leather</p>\r\n<p>hairy</p>\r\n<p>for sale</p>\r\n<p>beautiful</p>\r\n<p>country</p>\r\n<p>windy</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:27:31', '2019-07-22 00:29:09'),
(70, 5, 8, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences and include the adjective(s) in the correct place in each sentence.</p>\r\n<p>The house is for sale.&nbsp; (cute, little)</p>\r\n<p>It is a knife.&nbsp; (very, sharp)</p>\r\n<p>He is a man.&nbsp; (tall, handsome)</p>\r\n<p>It was a day yesterday.&nbsp; (cold, windy)</p>\r\n<p>They drink juice every morning.&nbsp; (prune)</p>\r\n<p>The bug is in my shoe.&nbsp; (big, green)</p>\r\n<p>Elizabeth is a teacher.&nbsp; (French)</p>\r\n<p>The spider is in the kitchen.&nbsp; (ugly, hairy)</p>\r\n<p>Canada is a country.&nbsp; (big, beautiful)</p>\r\n<p>The test was hard.&nbsp; (English)</p>\r\n<p>He was a policeman.&nbsp; (nice)</p>\r\n<p>Look at the snow.&nbsp; (beautiful, white)</p>\r\n<p>The frog is in the pond.&nbsp; (little, green)</p>\r\n<p>It was a whale.&nbsp; (huge)</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:29:30', '2019-07-22 00:33:01'),
(71, 5, 8, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 31', '<p><span >Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</span></p>\r\n<p>to make</p>\r\n<p>to hate</p>\r\n<p>to like</p>\r\n<p>to love</p>\r\n<p>to wear</p>\r\n<p>to need</p>\r\n<p>to watch</p>\r\n<p>to draw</p>\r\n<p>pie</p>\r\n<p>silver</p>\r\n<p>star</p>\r\n<p>watch</p>\r\n<p>junk</p>\r\n<p>sore</p>\r\n<p>food</p>\r\n<p>balloon</p>\r\n<p>rhubarb</p>\r\n<p>Mexican</p>\r\n<p>picture</p>\r\n<p>identical</p>\r\n<p>right</p>\r\n<p>cake</p>\r\n<p>BBQ</p>\r\n<p>knee</p>\r\n<p>wealthy</p>\r\n<p>dessert</p>\r\n<p>swollen</p>\r\n<p>left</p>\r\n<p>strawberry</p>\r\n<p>yogurt</p>\r\n<p>round</p>\r\n<p>chocolate</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:34:27', '2019-07-22 00:40:34'),
(72, 5, 8, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', 'Page 31', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences and include the adjective(s) in the correct place in the sentence.</p>\r\n<p>It was a winter.&nbsp; (long, hard)</p>\r\n<p>I need a watch.&nbsp; (new, silver)</p>\r\n<p>My hand is sore.&nbsp; (right)</p>\r\n<p>I want the balloons.&nbsp; (round)</p>\r\n<p>We like to watch movies.&nbsp; (old)</p>\r\n<p>Look at the star in the sky.&nbsp; (bright)</p>\r\n<p>I like chips.&nbsp; (BBQ)</p>\r\n<p>They want cake for dessert.&nbsp; (chocolate)</p>\r\n<p>I love food.&nbsp; (Mexican)</p>\r\n<p>He is a lawyer.&nbsp; (wealthy)</p>\r\n<p>You draw pictures.&nbsp; (funny)</p>\r\n<p>It was a meeting.&nbsp; (long, boring)</p>\r\n<p>My knee is swollen.&nbsp; (left)</p>\r\n<p>The kids like food.&nbsp; (junk)</p>\r\n<p>We like to make pies.&nbsp; (rhubarb)</p>\r\n<p>I hate yogurt.&nbsp; (strawberry)</p>\r\n<p>We wear shoes to school.&nbsp; (white)</p>\r\n<p>They are twins.&nbsp; (identical)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:36:00', '2019-07-22 00:39:23'),
(73, 2, 1, 6, 'Books and TV: New Phrases', NULL, 'escober--new-phrases', 'Phrases from the show.', '<p><span >cerciorarse </span><span >- ssegurarse de que se est&aacute; en lo cierto.</span></p>\r\n<p>azotar - derrotar, batir crema, envolver, dar con un l&aacute;tigo</p>\r\n<p>disque - disque muy dispuesto</p>\r\n<p>verraco - Cerdo macho que se utiliza como semental.&nbsp; Persona que se destaca por su fortaleza f&iacute;sica, audacia o valent&iacute;a.&nbsp; Persona que es vulgar, porfiado y necio.</p>\r\n<p>bobada - Dicho o hecho tonto o con poco fundamento, propio de un bobo.&nbsp; (Cuando est&aacute; nervioso dice muchas bobadas; fue una bobada dejar pasar esa oportunidad.)</p>\r\n<p>de por medio - in between; involucrado; en el medio.</p>\r\n<p>fundido - Agotado, muy cansado.</p>\r\n<p>lo que sea necesario - hacer todo lo necesario para lograr algo</p>\r\n<p>lo que fuera menester - whatever takes</p>\r\n<p>menester - Necesidad de una cosa.</p>\r\n<p>No es para menos - Es logico (No es para menos que lo despidieron, insult&oacute; al jefe y casi le pega).</p>\r\n<p>Es lo de menos - No es importante</p>\r\n<p>Inadaptados - juguetes inadaptados</p>\r\n<p>achacar - &iquest;No ser&aacute; que quieren achacar el muerto al tal Pablo?</p>\r\n<p>camellar - A camellar juiciosos, no quiero problemas.</p>\r\n<p>af&aacute;n - impaciencia, ansia, deseo, anhelo (Estoy muy de af&aacute;n.&nbsp;&nbsp;Estoy muy ansioso, impaciente).</p>\r\n<p>hagale pues - adelante</p>\r\n<p>contundente - abrumador (Que encierra tal convicci&oacute;n l&oacute;gica o se expone con tal energ&iacute;a que no deja lugar a la discusi&oacute;n.&nbsp; \"la contundente respuesta del ministro acall&oacute; las cr&iacute;ticas de la oposici&oacute;n.\")</p>\r\n<p>espeso/a - grueso, denso, tupido, gordo, cerrado</p>\r\n<p>estremecer - agitar, sacudir, temblar, mover, menear</p>\r\n<p>angusto/a - estrecho, angosto, reducido, peque&ntilde;o, restringido, corto</p>\r\n<p>liso - plano, fluido, tranquilo, llano, blando</p>\r\n<p>en fila india - single file</p>\r\n<p>bondadoso/a - ben&eacute;volo, cari&ntilde;oso, benigno, favorable</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 3, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 00:59:43', '2019-07-27 20:01:55'),
(74, 5, 9, 1, 'To Have: Present Tense', NULL, 'to-have--present-tense', NULL, '<p>Use the following to express the present tense of the verb&nbsp;<strong>To Have</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I have a red sharpener.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You have a beautiful living room.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He has a nice wife.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She has a blue toothbrush.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It has a small baby.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We have a swimming pool.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They have a new car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 07:57:53', '2019-07-25 22:18:40'),
(75, 5, 9, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 33', '<p>skill</p>\r\n<p>bad</p>\r\n<p>roof</p>\r\n<p>skirt</p>\r\n<p>headache</p>\r\n<p>dandruff</p>\r\n<p>sandwich</p>\r\n<p>day off</p>\r\n<p>eye shadow</p>\r\n<p>tail</p>\r\n<p>lunch</p>\r\n<p>weird</p>\r\n<p>week</p>\r\n<p>attitude</p>\r\n<p>terrible</p>\r\n<p>smile</p>\r\n<p>milk</p>\r\n<p>short</p>\r\n<p>next</p>\r\n<p>taste</p>\r\n<p>paw</p>\r\n<p>sleeping bag</p>\r\n<p>housekeeper</p>\r\n<p>peanut butter</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:01:02', '2019-07-22 08:02:00'),
(76, 5, 9, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', 'Page 34', '<p>He [have, has] a bad attitude.</p>\r\n<p>The cat [have, has] white paws.</p>\r\n<p>I [have, has] a peanut butter sandwich for lunch today.</p>\r\n<p>Maria [have, has] a red velvet skirt.</p>\r\n<p>We [have, has] a nice landlord.</p>\r\n<p>Jessica [have, has] a terrible headache.</p>\r\n<p>We [have, has] a good housekeeper.</p>\r\n<p>She [have, has] a lot of dandruff.</p>\r\n<p>Tony [have, has] very good skills.</p>\r\n<p>The milk [have, has] a weird taste.</p>\r\n<p>The house [have, has] a green roof.</p>\r\n<p>It [have, has] a short tail.</p>\r\n<p>We [have, has] a day off next week.</p>\r\n<p>I [have, has] a warm sleeping bag.</p>\r\n<p>My sister [have, has] purple eye shadow.</p>\r\n<p>You [have, has] a nice smile.</p>', 1, 4, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:02:29', '2019-07-25 04:25:27'),
(77, 5, 9, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 35', '<p>moose</p>\r\n<p>heartburn</p>\r\n<p>nail</p>\r\n<p>education</p>\r\n<p>kitten</p>\r\n<p>mailman</p>\r\n<p>same</p>\r\n<p>banana</p>\r\n<p>antlers</p>\r\n<p>letter</p>\r\n<p>parakeet</p>\r\n<p>scary</p>\r\n<p>duck</p>\r\n<p>helmet</p>\r\n<p>area code</p>\r\n<p>purse</p>\r\n<p>sunflower</p>\r\n<p>boyfriend</p>\r\n<p>motorcycle</p>\r\n<p>shorts</p>\r\n<p>puppy</p>\r\n<p>monkey</p>\r\n<p>kettle</p>\r\n<p>licorice</p>\r\n<p>seat</p>\r\n<p>bedroom</p>\r\n<p>cold (noun)</p>\r\n<p>rocking chair</p>\r\n<p>skate</p>\r\n<p>girlfriend</p>\r\n<p>duckling</p>\r\n<p>luggage</p>\r\n<p>braid</p>\r\n<p>mirror</p>\r\n<p>clock radio</p>\r\n<p>skipping rope</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:05:16', '2019-07-22 08:07:05'),
(78, 5, 9, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', 'Page 35', '<p>Complete the following sentences using <strong>has</strong> or <strong>have</strong> to form the present tense of the verb <strong>To Have</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ heartburn.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ a black helmet.</p>\r\n<p>Karina ___ long braids.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ rats in the basement.</p>\r\n<p>The monkey ___ a banana.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ a mirror in my purse.</p>\r\n<p>Jay ___ a fast motorcycle.</p>\r\n<p>My cat ___ two orange kittens.</p>\r\n<p>My sister ___ a boyfriend.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ a clock radio in my bedroom.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ leather seats.</p>\r\n<p>My aunt ___ a cold.</p>\r\n<p>Naomi ___ a skipping rope.</p>\r\n<p>Derek and Joe ___ black licorice.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ a white fridge.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ a bad report card this year.</p>\r\n<p>The moose ___ big antlers.</p>\r\n<p>Billy ___ blue shorts.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ sunflowers in the garden.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ a new kettle.</p>\r\n<p>The mailman ___ a letter for you.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ a new puppy.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ white skates.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ long nails.</p>\r\n<p>The duck ___ seven ducklings.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ the same area code.</p>\r\n<p>My brother ___ a new girlfriend.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ a lot of luggage.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ a good education.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ a rocking char in my living room.</p>\r\n<p>Nathan ___ a scary movie.</p>\r\n<p>Jason ___ a blue parakeet.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:07:24', '2019-07-22 08:12:20'),
(79, 5, 10, 1, 'To Have: Present Tense: Negative Form', NULL, 'to-have--present-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>do not</strong> or <strong>does not</strong> before the verb <strong>To Have</strong> to create a negative sentence.&nbsp; It is important to note that <strong>have</strong> is always used in the negative form and never <strong>has</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I do not have a dishwasher.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You do not have a pool.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he does not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He does not have a helmet.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she does not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She does not have braids.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it has</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it does not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It does not have white paws.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We do not have milk.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They do not have a daughter.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the present tense of the verb <strong>To Have</strong> can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>don\'t</strong> or <strong>doesn\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I don\'t have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>I don\'t have a headache.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>you don\'t have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>You don\'t have a flashlight.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he does not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>he doesn\'t have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>He doesn\'t have a pen.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she does not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>she doesn\'t have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>She doesn\'t have a lawyer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it does not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>it doesn\'t have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>It doesn\'t have a tail.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>we don\'t have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>We don\'t have a garage.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they do not have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>they don\'t have</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>They don\'t have a computer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:13:01', '2019-07-25 22:18:48'),
(80, 5, 10, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', 'Page 37', '<p>surprise</p>\r\n<p>bangs</p>\r\n<p>straight</p>\r\n<p>jewelry</p>\r\n<p>few</p>\r\n<p>flea</p>\r\n<p>fantastic</p>\r\n<p>customer</p>\r\n<p>clown</p>\r\n<p>antique</p>\r\n<p>nose</p>\r\n<p>about</p>\r\n<p>brother-in-law</p>\r\n<p>satellite dish</p>\r\n<p>screwdriver</p>\r\n<p>snowmobile</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:21:15', '2019-07-22 08:22:09'),
(81, 5, 10, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', 'Page 38', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the negative form of the verb <strong>To Have</strong>.&nbsp; Write the sentence once using <strong>do not</strong> or <strong>does not</strong> and once using the contraction <strong>don\'t</strong> or <strong>doesn\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>My cat has fleas.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We have a satellite dish on the roof.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I have a surprise for you.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Jimmy has a fast snowmobile.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We have many good books about antique jewelry.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>She has a lot of customers.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>My brother-in-law has a screwdriver.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>The clown has a big red nose.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I have long straight hair and bangs.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>She has fantastic news.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:22:27', '2019-07-22 08:25:33'),
(82, 5, 10, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 39', '<p>beard</p>\r\n<p>mean</p>\r\n<p>office</p>\r\n<p>shower</p>\r\n<p>landlady</p>\r\n<p>whisker</p>\r\n<p>fur</p>\r\n<p>glass</p>\r\n<p>horse</p>\r\n<p>ghost</p>\r\n<p>cell phone</p>\r\n<p>job</p>\r\n<p>saddle</p>\r\n<p>firecracker</p>\r\n<p>mouse</p>\r\n<p>relative</p>\r\n<p>doll</p>\r\n<p>treadmill</p>\r\n<p>bookmark</p>\r\n<p>nail file</p>\r\n<p>coat</p>\r\n<p>backyard</p>\r\n<p>curly</p>\r\n<p>ham</p>\r\n<p>pet</p>\r\n<p>trunk</p>\r\n<p>soft</p>\r\n<p>diamond</p>\r\n<p>filing cabinet</p>\r\n<p>dandelion</p>\r\n<p>keyboard</p>\r\n<p>German shepherd</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 08:25:56', '2019-07-22 08:27:32'),
(83, 5, 10, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', 'Page 39', '<p>Complete the following sentences using the contractions <strong>don\'t</strong> or <strong>doesn\'t</strong> to create the negative form of the verb <strong>To Have</strong> in the present tense.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ have curly hair.</p>\r\n<p>My aunt ___ have a diamond ring.</p>\r\n<p>Jennifer ___ have a doll.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ have a ham sandwich.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ have a new saddle for my horse.</p>\r\n<p>Glenn ___ have a boring job.</p>\r\n<p>The boys ___ have firecrackers.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ have a big back yard.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ have a cell phone.</p>\r\n<p>The cat ___ have soft fur.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ have relatives in New York.</p>\r\n<p>The mouse ___ have long whiskers.</p>\r\n<p>Samuel ___ have a new keyboard.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ have three pets.</p>\r\n<p>Richard ___ have a German shepherd.</p>\r\n<p>My car ___ have a big trunk.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ have a vacuum.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ have a question.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ have a nail file in my purse.</p>\r\n<p>My boss ___ have a filing cabinet.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ have a mean landlady.</p>\r\n<p>Derrick ___ have a beard.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ have a bookmark for her books.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ have a shower in the bathroom.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ have a fur coat.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ have many dandelions in the yard.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ have a treadnill in the basement.</p>\r\n<p>The teachers ___ have a meeting today.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ have a glass of red wine.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ have a ghost in the attic.</p>\r\n<p>Jason ___ have a car.</p>\r\n<p>Sharon ___ have a toothbrush.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 10:09:39', '2019-07-22 10:15:41'),
(13, 1, 2, 3, 'Simple Past Irregular Verbs 1', NULL, 'simple-past-irregular-verbs-1', 'The first list of irregular verbs.', '<p>The past tense of a normal verb ends in -ed such as looked, watched, opened, and closed.</p>\r\n<p>Irregular verbs are verbs which don\'t end in the standard -ed in the past tense.</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-note\">\r\n<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Irregular verbs don\'t have a pattern so they must be memorized.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>hide/hid</p>\r\n<p>drink/drank</p>\r\n<p>wear/wore</p>\r\n<p>go/went</p>\r\n<p>is/was</p>\r\n<p>feel/felt</p>\r\n<p>do/did</p>\r\n<p>bite/bit</p>\r\n<p>blow/blew</p>\r\n<p>shake/shook</p>\r\n<p>tear/tore</p>\r\n<p>slide/slid</p>\r\n<p>spend/spent</p>\r\n<p>teach/taught</p>\r\n<p>find/found</p>\r\n<p>fall/fell</p>\r\n<p>cut/cut</p>\r\n<p>break/broke</p>\r\n<p>buy/bought</p>\r\n<p>take/took</p>\r\n<p>speak/spoke</p>\r\n<p>hold/held</p>\r\n<p>pay/paid</p>\r\n<p>steal/stole</p>\r\n<p>hang/hung</p>\r\n<p>shoot/shot</p>\r\n<p>begin/began</p>\r\n<p>dig/dug</p>\r\n<p>draw/drew</p>\r\n<p>leave/left</p>\r\n<p>swear/swore</p>\r\n<p>sit/sat</p>\r\n<p>hear/heard</p>\r\n<p>see/saw</p>\r\n<p>give/gave</p>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-15 05:47:19', '2019-07-31 08:30:45'),
(14, 1, 2, 4, 'Simple Past Irregular Verbs 2', NULL, 'simple-past-irregular-verbs-2', 'The second list of irregular verbs.', '<p>The past tense of a normal verb ends in -ed such as looked, watched, opened, and closed.</p>\r\n<p>Irregular verbs are verbs which don\'t end in the standard -ed in the past tense.</p>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>lend/lent</p>\r\n<p>have/had</p>\r\n<p>drive/drove</p>\r\n<p>come/came</p>\r\n<p>wake/woke</p>\r\n<p>build/built</p>\r\n<p>forget/forgot</p>\r\n<p>freeze/froze</p>\r\n<p>catch/caught</p>\r\n<p>beat/beat</p>\r\n<p>ride/rode</p>\r\n<p>bend/bent</p>\r\n<p>sleep/slept</p>\r\n<p>understand/understood</p>\r\n<p>withdraw/withdrew</p>\r\n<p>shut/shut</p>\r\n<p>bring/brought</p>\r\n<p>win/won</p>\r\n<p>send/sent</p>\r\n<p>choose/chose</p>\r\n<p>grow/grew</p>\r\n<p>cost/cost</p>\r\n<p>forgive/forgave</p>\r\n<p>keep/kept</p>\r\n<p>rise/rose</p>\r\n<p>mean/meant</p>\r\n<p>hurt/hurt</p>\r\n<p>put/put</p>\r\n<p>lose/lost</p>\r\n<p>think/thought</p>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-15 05:49:13', '2019-07-31 08:31:02'),
(15, 1, 2, 5, 'Simple Past Irregular Verbs 3', NULL, 'simple-past-irregular-verbs-3', 'The third list of irregular verbs.', '<p>The past tense of a normal verb ends in -ed such as looked, watched, opened, and closed.</p>\r\n<p>Irregular verbs are verbs which don\'t end in the standard -ed in the past tense.</p>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>meet/met</p>\r\n<p>sing/sang</p>\r\n<p>ring/rang</p>\r\n<p>throw/threw</p>\r\n<p>run/ran</p>\r\n<p>get/got</p>\r\n<p>know/knew</p>\r\n<p>sell/sold</p>\r\n<p>spin/spun</p>\r\n<p>feed/fed</p>\r\n<p>fight/fought</p>\r\n<p>light/lit</p>\r\n<p>eat/ate</p>\r\n<p>fit/fit</p>\r\n<p>read/read</p>\r\n<p>swim/swam</p>\r\n<p>say/said</p>\r\n<p>tell/told</p>\r\n<p>hit/hit</p>\r\n<p>stick/stuck</p>\r\n<p>lead/led</p>\r\n<p>fly/flew</p>\r\n<p>weep/wept</p>\r\n<p>write/wrote</p>\r\n<p>sweep/swept</p>\r\n<p>stand/stood</p>\r\n<p>deal/dealt</p>\r\n<p>make/made</p>\r\n<p>quit/quit</p>\r\n<p>become/became.</p>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-15 05:50:58', '2019-07-31 08:31:24'),
(17, 1, 2, 2, 'Simple Past Regular Verbs', NULL, 'simple-past-regular-verbs', NULL, '<p>Typically, to make a verb work in the past, you simply add -ed to the end of it, for example:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>walk - walk<strong>ed</strong></p>\r\n<p>talk - talk<strong>ed</strong></p>\r\n<p>wash - wash<strong>ed</strong></p>\r\n<p>look - look<strong>ed</strong></p>\r\n<p>watch - watch<strong>ed</strong></p>\r\n<p>start - start<strong>ed</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>If a verb ends in -e, just add -d.</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>live - live<strong>d</strong></p>\r\n<p>date - date<strong>d</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>If a verb ends in -y, change the -y to -i and then add -ed.</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>marry - marr<strong>ied</strong></p>\r\n<p>carry - carr<strong>ied</strong></p>\r\n<p>try - tr<strong>ied</strong></p>\r\n<p>cry - cr<strong>ied</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>If a one-syllable verb ends in a single vowel and then a consonant, double the consonant and then add -ed.</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>stop - stop<strong>ped</strong></p>\r\n<p>plan - plan<strong>ned</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Here are examples of using the simple past tense:</p>\r\n<div class=\"lesson-examples\">\r\n<p>I <strong>wash</strong> the plates every day.<br />Yesterday I <strong>washed</strong> the glasses.</p>\r\n<p>I <strong>talk</strong> to him every day.<br />Yesterday, I <strong>talked</strong> to her.</p>\r\n<p>He <strong>watches</strong> TV on Monday.<br />Yesterday, he <strong>watched</strong> a movie.</p>\r\n<p>They <strong>watch</strong> movies every week.<br />Last week, they <strong>watched</strong> Star Wars.</p>\r\n<p>We <strong>look</strong> for the newspaper every Sunday.<br />Last Sunday, we <strong>looked</strong> for it.</p>\r\n<p>He <strong>lives</strong> here now.<br />Last year, he <strong>lived</strong> in New York.</p>\r\n<p>You <strong>try</strong> new food every week.<br />Last week, you <strong>tried</strong> Thai food.</p>\r\n<p>They always <strong>stop</strong> at night.<br />Yesterday they <strong>stopped</strong> in the afternoon.</p>\r\n<p>She <strong>plans</strong> lunch every morning.<br />Yesterday, she <strong>planned</strong> lunch at night.</p>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-15 22:36:37', '2019-07-31 08:30:45'),
(87, 5, 11, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', 'Page 42', '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions by placing <strong>do</strong> or <strong>does</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>You have a pink eraser.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>He has my phone number.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>They have everything they need.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We have the same scarf.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I have rights.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Marissa has green flip-flops.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>You have a huge turkey for Thanksgiving.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>They have a lease until next year.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>It has a funny taste.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>You have two important appointments today.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>The dove has white wings.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We have a day off next week.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>David has a pager.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Juanita has a good recipe for meat loaf.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We have a tight deadline for the project.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>They have a big celebration on Chirstmas Eve.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 23:28:16', '2019-07-22 23:32:02'),
(88, 5, 11, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 43', '<p>mud</p>\r\n<p>tire</p>\r\n<p>gold</p>\r\n<p>claw</p>\r\n<p>glasses</p>\r\n<p>manager</p>\r\n<p>leg</p>\r\n<p>flat</p>\r\n<p>wrong</p>\r\n<p>Germany</p>\r\n<p>map</p>\r\n<p>better</p>\r\n<p>marshmallow</p>\r\n<p>e-mail address</p>\r\n<p>bathrobe</p>\r\n<p>ladybug</p>\r\n<p>necklace</p>\r\n<p>bib</p>\r\n<p>shirt</p>\r\n<p>mattress</p>\r\n<p>receipt</p>\r\n<p>noodle</p>\r\n<p>tie</p>\r\n<p>show</p>\r\n<p>time</p>\r\n<p>dictionary</p>\r\n<p>tooth</p>\r\n<p>ant</p>\r\n<p>bruise</p>\r\n<p>eye</p>\r\n<p>poodle</p>\r\n<p>membership</p>\r\n<p>fax machine</p>\r\n<p>cousin</p>\r\n<p>binoculars</p>\r\n<p>gym</p>\r\n<p>beaver</p>\r\n<p>silk</p>\r\n<p>polka dot</p>\r\n<p>scar</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 23:32:15', '2019-07-22 23:33:48'),
(89, 5, 11, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', 'Page 43', '<p>Complete the following questions with <strong>do</strong> or <strong>does</strong> to create the question form in the present tense with the verb <strong>To Have</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>___ I have lipstick on my tooth?</p>\r\n<p>___ you have a new mattress?</p>\r\n<p>___ Mike have a black tie?</p>\r\n<p>___ the kids have a bag of marshmallows?</p>\r\n<p>___ he have the wrong answer?</p>\r\n<p>___ I have a bruise on my arm?</p>\r\n<p>___ he have a membership for the gym?</p>\r\n<p>___ we have binoculars for the show?</p>\r\n<p>___ the soup have a lot of noodles?</p>\r\n<p>___ it have green eyes?</p>\r\n<p>___ you have a better map of the city?</p>\r\n<p>___ they have a poodle?</p>\r\n<p>___ Carlos have my e-mail address?</p>\r\n<p>___ we have winter tires?</p>\r\n<p>___ the horse have a saddle?</p>\r\n<p>___ it have pink polka dots?</p>\r\n<p>___ she have a silk bathrobe?</p>\r\n<p>___ the beaver have a flat tail?</p>\r\n<p>___ I have a scar on my leg?</p>\r\n<p>___ we have a new manager today?</p>\r\n<p>___ she have a cousin in Germany?</p>\r\n<p>___ you have the receipt in the bag?</p>\r\n<p>___ Shaun have new glasses?</p>\r\n<p>___ I have a ladybug on my shirt?</p>\r\n<p>___ Samantha have a gold necklace?</p>\r\n<p>___ we have ants in the basement?</p>\r\n<p>___ I have mud on my shoes?</p>\r\n<p>___ you have a dictionary?</p>\r\n<p>___ they have a fax machine?</p>\r\n<p>___ you have a bib for the baby?</p>\r\n<p>___ I have the right time?</p>\r\n<p>___ the cat have sharp claws?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-22 23:34:05', '2019-07-22 23:39:21'),
(16, 3, 2, 1, 'Sample Format', NULL, 'sample-format', NULL, '<p>Responsive Table</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table lesson-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Zero</th>\r\n<th>Zero</th>\r\n<th>Zero</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>one</td>\r\n<td>one</td>\r\n<td>one</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>two</td>\r\n<td>two</td>\r\n<td>two</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>three</td>\r\n<td>three</td>\r\n<td>three</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-15 18:37:59', '2019-08-04 01:04:29'),
(18, 2, 2, 3, 'Frases Avanzadas en Español 3', NULL, 'frases-advansadas-en-espanol-3', 'El último vocabulario avanzado en español', '<p>Espero saber algo hoy (subjuntivo) - Espero que sepas algo hoy</p>\r\n<p>Espero tener un buen dia&nbsp;(subjuntivo)&nbsp;- Espero que tengas un buen d&iacute;a</p>\r\n<p>Palabras cortas con accento - M&aacute;s d&iacute;a, as&iacute;</p>\r\n<p>Espero que quieras ir (en pasado) -&nbsp; Esperaba que quisieras ir.</p>\r\n<p>Quiero que me quieras (en pasado) -&nbsp; Quer&iacute;a que me quisieras.</p>\r\n<p>alta presi&oacute;n sangu&iacute;nea - presi&oacute;n alta de la sangre.</p>\r\n<p>avaro - persona que ans&iacute;a poseer muchas riquezas por el solo placer de atesorarlas sin compartirlas con nadie.</p>\r\n<p>desaguar, desag&uuml;e - Sacar el agua que hay en un lugar.</p>\r\n<p>verter - Hacer pasar un l&iacute;quido o una materia disgregada de un recipiente a otro.</p>\r\n<p>disgregar - Desincorporar; Separar o desunir los elementos que forman un conjunto o las partes de una cosa.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>untar &ndash; Cubrir la superficie de una cosa con una sustancia grasa.</p>\r\n<p>sazonar - poner sabores / condimentos.</p>\r\n<p>Abrir la caja de los truenos - can of worms</p>\r\n<p>En un abrir y cerrar de ojos - ojo parpadeante.&nbsp; algo que pasa muy rapido.</p>\r\n<p>Jug&aacute;rsela a cara o cruz &ndash; tirar una moneda</p>\r\n<p>No se gan&oacute; Zamora en una hora - Roma no fue construida en un d&iacute;a.</p>\r\n<p>Con las manos en la masa - encontrado con manos enrojecidas</p>\r\n<p>Andar en las nubes - dispistado.&nbsp; andar con la cabeza en las nubes</p>\r\n<p>Ojos que no ven, coraz&oacute;n que no siente - refr&aacute;n espa&ntilde;ol que se refiere a que las personas no sufren por lo que no saben.&nbsp; &nbsp;out of sight, out of mind.</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-18 04:47:42', '2020-01-31 01:54:35');
