(111, 5, 15, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', 'Page 59', '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to ride</p>\r\n<p>to fry</p>\r\n<p>to sail</p>\r\n<p>to sell</p>\r\n<p>to fly</p>\r\n<p>to greet</p>\r\n<p>to give</p>\r\n<p>to protect</p>\r\n<p>to curl</p>\r\n<p>to leave</p>\r\n<p>to argue</p>\r\n<p>to cut</p>\r\n<p>to hang</p>\r\n<p>to lace</p>\r\n<p>to use</p>\r\n<p>to demand</p>\r\n<p>world</p>\r\n<p>boat</p>\r\n<p>sand</p>\r\n<p>market</p>\r\n<p>around</p>\r\n<p>water</p>\r\n<p>bike</p>\r\n<p>field</p>\r\n<p>head</p>\r\n<p>skate</p>\r\n<p>lawn mower</p>\r\n<p>freedom</p>\r\n<p>day care</p>\r\n<p>footprint</p>\r\n<p>fireman</p>\r\n<p>kite</p>\r\n<p>week</p>\r\n<p>skim</p>\r\n<p>diary</p>\r\n<p>boot</p>\r\n<p>curling iron</p>\r\n<p>sunglasses</p>\r\n<p>arena</p>\r\n<p>fireplace</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:29:47', '2019-07-25 21:31:30'),
(112, 5, 15, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', 'Page 59', '<p>Complete the sentences using the correct possessive adjective according to the subject.</p>\r\n<p>They sail ___ boat around the world. - their</p>\r\n<p>She fries ___ eggs in butter. - her</p>\r\n<p>We give ___ old cothes to Peter. - our</p>\r\n<p>I ride ___ bike to school. - my</p>\r\n<p>She curls ___ hair with a curling iron. - her</p>\r\n<p>You need ___ dark sunglasses. - your</p>\r\n<p>I lace ___ skates at the arena. - my</p>\r\n<p>It drinks ___ water. - its</p>\r\n<p>We sell ___ vegetables at the market. - our</p>\r\n<p>The fireman wears ___ black boots - his</p>\r\n<p>The twins love and protect ___ brother. - their</p>\r\n<p>I greet ___ guests. - my</p>\r\n<p>They argue with ___ neighbors. - their</p>\r\n<p>He needs ___ lawyer. - his</p>\r\n<p>We demand ___ rights. - our</p>\r\n<p>He uses ___ lawn mower to cut the grass. - his</p>\r\n<p>I scratch ___ head. - my</p>\r\n<p>She hangs ___ clothes on the clothesline. - her</p>\r\n<p>They clean ___ fireplace every week. - their</p>\r\n<p>I drink ___ tea with skim milk. - my</p>\r\n<p>Laura loves ___ husband. - her</p>\r\n<p>You want ___ freedom. - your</p>\r\n<p>We leave ___ kids at the daycare. - our</p>\r\n<p>She writes in ___ diary. - her</p>\r\n<p>He flies ___ kite in the wind. - his</p>\r\n<p>I see ___ footprints in the sand. - my</p>', 1, 5, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:31:46', '2019-07-25 21:40:44'),
(113, 5, 16, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense', NULL, 'the-simple-past-tense', NULL, '<p>The simple past is used to describe an action that happened in the recent past.&nbsp; Follow these rules to create the simple past tense with regular verbs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add -ed to the simple form of the verb.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Visit</strong></p>\r\n<p>I visited</p>\r\n<p>you visited</p>\r\n<p>he visited</p>\r\n<p>she visited</p>\r\n<p>it visited</p>\r\n<p>we visited</p>\r\n<p>they visited</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add only -d if the verb ends in e.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Believe</strong></p>\r\n<p>I believed</p>\r\n<p>you believed</p>\r\n<p>he believed</p>\r\n<p>she believed</p>\r\n<p>it believed</p>\r\n<p>we believed</p>\r\n<p>they believed</p>\r\n<p><strong>Delete y and add -ied if the verb ends in y preceded by a consonant.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Cry</strong></p>\r\n<p>I cried</p>\r\n<p>you cried</p>\r\n<p>he cried</p>\r\n<p>she cried</p>\r\n<p>it cried</p>\r\n<p>we cried</p>\r\n<p>they cried</p>\r\n<h3>Pronunciation</h3>\r\n<p><strong>When -ed is added to verb that end in d, pronounce the last syllable separately.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Need</strong></p>\r\n<p>I need-ed</p>\r\n<p>you need-ed</p>\r\n<p>he need-ed</p>\r\n<p>she need-ed</p>\r\n<p>it need-ed</p>\r\n<p>we need-ed</p>\r\n<p>they need-ed</p>\r\n<p><strong>When -ed is added to verbs that end in t, pronounce the last syllable separately.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Want</strong></p>\r\n<p>I want-ed</p>\r\n<p>you want-ed</p>\r\n<p>he want-ed</p>\r\n<p>she want-ed</p>\r\n<p>it want-ed</p>\r\n<p>we want-ed</p>\r\n<p>they want-ed</p>\r\n<p><strong>The ending of all other regular verbs is pronounced as one syllable when -ed is added.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Open</strong></p>\r\n<p>I opened</p>\r\n<p>you opened</p>\r\n<p>he opened</p>\r\n<p>she opened</p>\r\n<p>it opened</p>\r\n<p>we opened</p>\r\n<p>they opened</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:42:18', '2019-07-25 22:16:06'),
(114, 5, 16, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to answer</p>\r\n<p>to increase</p>\r\n<p>to share</p>\r\n<p>to kill</p>\r\n<p>to try</p>\r\n<p>to lie</p>\r\n<p>to reward</p>\r\n<p>to notice</p>\r\n<p>to land</p>\r\n<p>to dry</p>\r\n<p>to sign</p>\r\n<p>to challenge</p>\r\n<p>hair dryer</p>\r\n<p>upside down</p>\r\n<p>snack</p>\r\n<p>lease</p>\r\n<p>age</p>\r\n<p>ditch</p>\r\n<p>inside out</p>\r\n<p>another</p>\r\n<p>eel</p>\r\n<p>toad</p>\r\n<p>building</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:52:12', '2019-07-25 21:53:34'),
(115, 5, 16, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the simple past tense by adding -ed or -ied to the simple form of the verb in parenthesis.</p>\r\n<p>I (to use) my hair dryer to dry my hair. - used</p>\r\n<p>We (to try) a new recipe last night. - tried</p>\r\n<p>Thomas (to answer) the phone. - answered</p>\r\n<p>I (to notice) that your sweated was inside out. - noticed</p>\r\n<p>The car (to land) upside down in the ditch. - landed</p>\r\n<p>She (to share) her snack with her friends at school yesterday. - shared</p>\r\n<p>The minimum wage (to increase) last year. - increased</p>\r\n<p>Suzanne (to lie) about her age. - lied</p>\r\n<p>My company (to sign) the lease for our building for another three years - signed</p>\r\n<p>The teacher (to challenge) her students to work hard. - challenged</p>\r\n<p>The snake (to kill) the frog. - killed</p>', 1, 30, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 21:53:49', '2019-07-25 22:55:23'),
(116, 5, 16, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>to destry</p>\r\n<p>to describe</p>\r\n<p>to rain</p>\r\n<p>to knock</p>\r\n<p>to borrow</p>\r\n<p>to avoid</p>\r\n<p>to move</p>\r\n<p>to tidy</p>\r\n<p>to decide</p>\r\n<p>to obtain</p>\r\n<p>to please</p>\r\n<p>to expect</p>\r\n<p>to serve</p>\r\n<p>to deny</p>\r\n<p>to accept</p>\r\n<p>to marry</p>\r\n<p>to arrest</p>\r\n<p>to prove</p>\r\n<p>to join</p>\r\n<p>to paint</p>\r\n<p>in-line skates</p>\r\n<p>contract</p>\r\n<p>lawn</p>\r\n<p>accident</p>\r\n<p>everybody</p>\r\n<p>in detail</p>\r\n<p>someone</p>\r\n<p>weekend</p>\r\n<p>terms</p>\r\n<p>audience</p>\r\n<p>innocent</p>\r\n<p>plain</p>\r\n<p>army</p>\r\n<p>door</p>\r\n<p>makeup</p>\r\n<p>collision</p>\r\n<p>doctor</p>\r\n<p>conditions</p>\r\n<p>passport</p>\r\n<p>court</p>\r\n<p>alert</p>\r\n<p>appetizer</p>\r\n<p>singer</p>\r\n<p>police</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 22:02:22', '2019-07-25 22:04:24'),
(117, 5, 16, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the sentences using the simple past tense by adding <strong>-ed</strong> or <strong>-ied</strong> to the simple form of these regular verbs.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to accept) the terms and conditions of the contract. - accepted</p>\r\n<p>My brother ___ (to join) the army. - joined</p>\r\n<p>My neighbors ___ (to move) to Vancouver. - moved</p>\r\n<p>Someone ___ (to knock) on the door. - knocked</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to describe) the accident in detail. - described</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to prove) that I was innocent in court. - proved</p>\r\n<p>The man ___ (to deny) everything. - denied</p>\r\n<p>Tina ___ (to borrow) my in-line skates. - borrowed</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (to watch) the kids in the pool. - watched</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to use) my makeup. - used</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to tidy) the house for my mother. - tidied</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to rain) all day. - rained</p>\r\n<p>My husband ___ (to paint) the bathroom on the weekend. - painted</p>\r\n<p>I was alert and I ___ (to avoid) the collision. - avoided</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to push) the baby in the carriage. - pushed</p>\r\n<p>My cousin ___ (to marry) a doctor. - married</p>\r\n<p>The singer ___ (to please) the audience. - pleased</p>\r\n<p>Your dog ___ (to destory) my lawn. - destroyed</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to serve) appetizers to our guests. - served</p>\r\n<p>Mike ___ (to obtain) his passport. - obtained</p>\r\n<p>The police ___ (to arrest) everybody. - arrested</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to order) a plain pizza last night. - ordered</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to decide) to learn English. - decided</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to expect) to see you there. - expected</p>', 1, 30, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-25 22:04:41', '2019-07-25 22:57:23'),
(119, 5, 17, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>felt (to feel)</p>\r\n<p>bit (to bite)</p>\r\n<p>blew (to blow)</p>\r\n<p>shook (to shake)</p>\r\n<p>tore (to tear)</p>\r\n<p>slid (to slide)</p>\r\n<p>spent (to spend)</p>\r\n<p>taught (to teach)</p>\r\n<p>did (to do)</p>\r\n<p>found (to find)</p>\r\n<p>fell (to fall)</p>\r\n<p>cut (to cut)</p>\r\n<p>broke (to break)</p>\r\n<p>bought (to buy)</p>\r\n<p>took (to take)</p>\r\n<p>honeymoon</p>\r\n<p>earthquake</p>\r\n<p>grandparent</p>\r\n<p>toboggan</p>\r\n<p>Ireland</p>\r\n<p>finger</p>\r\n<p>mountain</p>\r\n<p>when</p>\r\n<p>pants</p>\r\n<p>math</p>\r\n<p>dishes</p>\r\n<p>saw</p>\r\n<p>cup</p>\r\n<p>overseas</p>\r\n<p>down</p>\r\n<p>favorite</p>\r\n<p>high school</p>\r\n<p>after</p>\r\n<p>gift</p>\r\n<p>ankle</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 00:03:27', '2019-07-26 00:06:36'),
(120, 5, 17, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irrgular past tense form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>She (to blow) on her soup because it was hot. - blew</p>\r\n<p>The house (to shake) a lot during the earthquake. - shook</p>\r\n<p>They (to take) the plane for their honeymoon overseas. - took</p>\r\n<p>We (to spend) our time shopping. - spent</p>\r\n<p>I always (to feel) sick when I was pregnant. - felt</p>\r\n<p>He (to tear) his pants. - tore</p>\r\n<p>We (to buy) a nice gift for our grandparents. - bought</p>\r\n<p>The kids (to slide) down the mountain. - slid</p>\r\n<p>I (to do) the dishes after supper. - did</p>\r\n<p>I (to cut) my finger on the sharp saw. - cut</p>\r\n<p>You (to break) my favorite cup. - broke</p>\r\n<p>Your dog (to bite) my ankle. - bit</p>\r\n<p>Karen (to find) a purse at the beach. - found</p>\r\n<p>I (to teach) math at the high school last year. - taught</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 00:06:54', '2019-07-26 00:12:01'),
(121, 5, 17, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>spoke (to speak)</p>\r\n<p>held (to hold)</p>\r\n<p>paid (to pay)</p>\r\n<p>stole (to steal)</p>\r\n<p>hung (to hang)</p>\r\n<p>shot (to shoot)</p>\r\n<p>began (to begin)</p>\r\n<p>dugg&nbsp; (to dig)</p>\r\n<p>drew (to draw)</p>\r\n<p>left (to leave)</p>\r\n<p>swore (to swear)</p>\r\n<p>sat (to sit)</p>\r\n<p>heard (to hear)</p>\r\n<p>saw (to see)</p>\r\n<p>gave (to give)</p>\r\n<p>niece</p>\r\n<p>front</p>\r\n<p>store</p>\r\n<p>whistle</p>\r\n<p>thing</p>\r\n<p>pantry</p>\r\n<p>bored</p>\r\n<p>witch</p>\r\n<p>plastic</p>\r\n<p>broom</p>\r\n<p>great</p>\r\n<p>swing</p>\r\n<p>speech</p>\r\n<p>calculator</p>\r\n<p>problem</p>\r\n<p>tunnel</p>\r\n<p>midnight</p>\r\n<p>party</p>\r\n<p>stop sign</p>\r\n<p>shoplifter</p>\r\n<p>crossing guard</p>\r\n<p>pink flamingo</p>\r\n<p>nephew</p>\r\n<p>underground</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:15:26', '2019-07-26 01:18:33'),
(122, 5, 17, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb indicated in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>The teachers ___ (to speak) about the computer problems. - spoke</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to begin) my homework after school. - began</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to give) money to his neice. - gave</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to hang) the whistle around he neck. - hung</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to see) the shoplifter in the store. - saw</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to sit) on the swing and talked. - sat</p>\r\n<p>Somebody ___ (to steal) my pencil at school. - stole</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to pay) a lot of money for the book. - paid</p>\r\n<p>Cheyenne ___ (to draw) a nice picture of a tree. - drew</p>\r\n<p>David ___ (to swear) in class today. - swore</p>\r\n<p>The workers ___ (to dig) a big tunnel. - dug</p>\r\n<p>The crossing guard ___ (to hold) the stop sign. - held</p>\r\n<p>The police ___ (to shoot) the man in the leg. - shot</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to hear) your speech last night. - heard</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (to leave) the party late. - left</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to see) a mouse. - saw</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:19:26', '2019-07-26 01:24:17'),
(123, 5, 18, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense with Irregular Verbs: 2', NULL, 'the-simple-past-tense-with-irregular-verbs--2', NULL, '<p>Some verbs do not use the <strong>-ed</strong> ending to express the past tense.&nbsp; These are irregular verbs, and they have unique past tense forms.&nbsp; They have the same form for all persons in the past tense, and they must be memorized.</p>\r\n<p>To Have (had)</p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they had</p>\r\n<p>To Lend (lent)</p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they lent</p>\r\n<p>To Drive (drove)</p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they drove</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:32:18', '2019-07-26 01:34:39'),
(124, 5, 18, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>had (to have)</p>\r\n<p>lent (to lend)</p>\r\n<p>drove (to drive)</p>\r\n<p>came (to come)</p>\r\n<p>woke (to wake)</p>\r\n<p>built (to build)</p>\r\n<p>forgot (to forget)</p>\r\n<p>froze (to freeze)</p>\r\n<p>caught (to catch)</p>\r\n<p>beat (to beat)</p>\r\n<p>rode (to ride)</p>\r\n<p>bent (to bend)</p>\r\n<p>slept (to sleep)</p>\r\n<p>understood (to understand)</p>\r\n<p>withdrew (to withdraw)</p>\r\n<p>bacon</p>\r\n<p>stamp</p>\r\n<p>rifle</p>\r\n<p>sheep</p>\r\n<p>hay</p>\r\n<p>first</p>\r\n<p>lunch</p>\r\n<p>barn</p>\r\n<p>cheese</p>\r\n<p>bullfrog</p>\r\n<p>hanger</p>\r\n<p>hunter</p>\r\n<p>lamb</p>\r\n<p>bagel</p>\r\n<p>month</p>\r\n<p>whole</p>\r\n<p>enough</p>\r\n<p>tadpole</p>\r\n<p>envelope</p>\r\n<p>post office</p>\r\n<p>sand castle</p>\r\n<p>warehouse</p>\r\n<p>inventory</p>\r\n<p>lettuce</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:34:51', '2019-07-26 01:37:42'),
(125, 5, 18, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentence in the simple past tense using the past tense form of the irregular verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to withdraw) enough money for the whole month. - withdrew</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to catch) a bullfrog and four tadpoles in the pond. - caught</p>\r\n<p>Salina ___ (to ride) a horse yesterday. - rode</p>\r\n<p>Robert ___ (to build) a huge sand castle on the beach. - built</p>\r\n<p>Brandon ___ (to bend) the hanger to open the car door. - bent</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to drive) my new car yesterday. - drove</p>\r\n<p>The hunter ___ (to forget) his rifle in the woods. - forgot</p>\r\n<p>You ___ (to wake) your grandmother when you knocked. - woke</p>\r\n<p>The sheep and lamb ___ (to sleep) on the hay in the barn. - slept</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to have) a bagel with bacon for lunch. - had</p>\r\n<p>Camilie ___ (to understand) what the teacher taught in class today. - understood</p>\r\n<p>My mother ___ (to freeze) the vegetables for the winter. - froze</p>\r\n<p>Dimitri ___ (to lend) the shovel to his neighbor. - lent</p>\r\n<p>The red team ___ (to beat) the blue team. - beat</p>\r\n<p>Laurent ___ (to come) to help us with the inventory in the warehouse. - came</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:37:51', '2019-07-26 01:43:37'),
(126, 5, 18, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>shut (to shut)</p>\r\n<p>brought (to bring)</p>\r\n<p>won (to win)</p>\r\n<p>sent (to send)</p>\r\n<p>chose (to choose)</p>\r\n<p>grew (to grow)</p>\r\n<p>cost (to cost)</p>\r\n<p>forgave (to forgive)</p>\r\n<p>kept (to keep)</p>\r\n<p>rose (to rise)</p>\r\n<p>meant (to mean)</p>\r\n<p>hurt (to hurt)</p>\r\n<p>put (to put)</p>\r\n<p>lost (to lose)</p>\r\n<p>thought (to think)</p>\r\n<p>package</p>\r\n<p>cookie</p>\r\n<p>early</p>\r\n<p>toe</p>\r\n<p>cauliflower</p>\r\n<p>gorgeous</p>\r\n<p>joke</p>\r\n<p>park</p>\r\n<p>nail</p>\r\n<p>screw</p>\r\n<p>weed</p>\r\n<p>cabbage</p>\r\n<p>bride</p>\r\n<p>gardener</p>\r\n<p>hearing aid</p>\r\n<p>deaf</p>\r\n<p>hand</p>\r\n<p>airmail</p>\r\n<p>umbrella</p>\r\n<p>blind</p>\r\n<p>groom</p>\r\n<p>gift certificate</p>\r\n<p>even enough</p>\r\n<p>as</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:43:58', '2019-07-26 01:47:22'),
(127, 5, 18, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb indicated in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to bring) my umbrella when we went for a walk in the park. - brought</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to cost) a lot but it was gorgeous and we loved it. - cost</p>\r\n<p>The sun ___ (to rise) early this morning. - rose</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to win) a gift certificate at the Christmas party. - won</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to grow) cabbages, cauliflowers, and pumpkins in our garden last summer. - grew</p>\r\n<p>The gardener ___ (to put) the weeds in the garbage can. - put</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to mean) that as a joke. - meant</p>\r\n<p>Jasmin ___ (to shut) the door on her toe. - shut</p>\r\n<p>The bride and groom ___ (to choose) a beautiful wedding cake. - chose</p>\r\n<p>Even though he lied, she ___ (to forgive) him. - forgave</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to think) you liked peas. - thought</p>\r\n<p>Sharon is blind and deaf and she ___ (to lose) her hearing aid.</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to hurt) when the cat scratched my hand. - hurt</p>\r\n<p>My father ___ (to keep) the nails and screws in jars in the garage. - kept</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to send) the package by airmail. - sent</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to drink) milk with our cookies. - drank</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 01:47:31', '2019-07-26 01:52:42'),
(128, 5, 19, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense with Irregular Verbs: 3', NULL, 'the-simple-past-tense-with-irregular-verbs--3', NULL, '<p>Some verbs do not use the -ed ending to express the past tense.&nbsp; These are irregular verbs, and they have unique past tense forms.&nbsp; They have the same form for all persons in the past tense, and they must be memorized.</p>\r\n<p><strong>To Meet</strong> &rarr; <strong>met</strong></p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they <strong>met</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Sing</strong> &rarr; <strong>sang</strong></p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they <strong>sang</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>To Ring</strong> &rarr; <strong>rang</strong></p>\r\n<p>I/you/he/she/it/we/they <strong>rang</strong></p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:08:12', '2019-07-26 02:11:31'),
(129, 5, 19, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to meet &rarr; met</p>\r\n<p>to sing &rarr; sang</p>\r\n<p>to ring &rarr; rang</p>\r\n<p>to throw &rarr; threw</p>\r\n<p>to run &rarr; ran</p>\r\n<p>to get &rarr; got</p>\r\n<p>to know &rarr; knew</p>\r\n<p>to sell &rarr; sold</p>\r\n<p>to spin &rarr; spun</p>\r\n<p>to feed &rarr; fed</p>\r\n<p>to fight &rarr; fought</p>\r\n<p>to light &rarr; lit</p>\r\n<p>to eat &rarr; ate</p>\r\n<p>to fit &rarr; fit</p>\r\n<p>to read &rarr; read</p>\r\n<p>fire</p>\r\n<p>too</p>\r\n<p>ice</p>\r\n<p>guilty</p>\r\n<p>crime</p>\r\n<p>paper</p>\r\n<p>noisy</p>\r\n<p>parrot</p>\r\n<p>middle</p>\r\n<p>icing</p>\r\n<p>Monday</p>\r\n<p>Tuesday</p>\r\n<p>Wednesday</p>\r\n<p>Thursday</p>\r\n<p>Friday</p>\r\n<p>Saturday</p>\r\n<p>Sunday</p>\r\n<p>raise</p>\r\n<p>evening</p>\r\n<p>liquor store</p>\r\n<p>power failure</p>\r\n<p>out of control</p>\r\n<p>concert</p>\r\n<p>phone</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:11:58', '2019-07-26 02:15:19'),
(130, 5, 19, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to sing) on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday at the concert in Montreal. - sang</p>\r\n<p>The house was dark because of the power failure so we ___ (to light) the candles. - lit</p>\r\n<p>The car ___ (to spin) out of control on the ice. - spun</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to read) the newspaper in the evening on Saturday and Sunday. - read</p>\r\n<p>My son ___ (to fight) at school on Tuesday and Thursday last week. - fought</p>\r\n<p>The phone ___ (to ring) in the middle of the night. - rang</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to know) that he was guilty of the crime. - knew</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to meet) Sara at the liquor store. - met</p>\r\n<p>Sorry, but I ___ (to eat) all the icing on your cake when you went to the bathroom. - ate</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to get) a big raise at work last month. - got</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to sell) our parrot because he was too noisy. - sold</p>\r\n<p>Alexandre ___ (to throw) the papers in the fire. - threw</p>\r\n<p>My pants ___ (to fit) last year. - fit</p>\r\n<p>Carmen ___ (to run) and hid under the bed. - ran</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to feed) meat to the fox. - fed</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:15:32', '2019-07-26 02:20:47'),
(131, 5, 19, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following irregular verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to swim &rarr; swam</p>\r\n<p>to say &rarr; said</p>\r\n<p>to tell &rarr; told</p>\r\n<p>to hit &rarr; hit</p>\r\n<p>to stick &rarr; stuck</p>\r\n<p>to lead &rarr; led</p>\r\n<p>to fly &rarr; flew</p>\r\n<p>to weep &rarr; wept</p>\r\n<p>to write &rarr; wrote</p>\r\n<p>to sweep &rarr; swept</p>\r\n<p>to stand &rarr; stood</p>\r\n<p>to deal &rarr; dealt</p>\r\n<p>to make &rarr; made</p>\r\n<p>to quit &rarr; quit</p>\r\n<p>to become &rarr; became</p>\r\n<p>sidewalk</p>\r\n<p>dentures</p>\r\n<p>wall</p>\r\n<p>date</p>\r\n<p>snowman</p>\r\n<p>minute</p>\r\n<p>corner</p>\r\n<p>chalk</p>\r\n<p>piece</p>\r\n<p>blackboard</p>\r\n<p>glue</p>\r\n<p>dolphine</p>\r\n<p>issue</p>\r\n<p>truth</p>\r\n<p>stream</p>\r\n<p>prnicess</p>\r\n<p>jury</p>\r\n<p>drink</p>\r\n<p>housecoat</p>\r\n<p>on vacation</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:21:14', '2019-07-26 02:23:56'),
(132, 5, 19, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences in the simple past tense using the irregular past tense form of the verb indicated in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to deal) with many issues at work yesterday. - dealt</p>\r\n<p>I thought you ___ (to say) it was free. - said</p>\r\n<p>Liliane ___ (to sweep) the sidewalk with her new broom. - swept</p>\r\n<p>The kindergarten class ___ (to make) a snowman this morning. - made</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to stick) the pieces of wood together with glue. - stuck</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to hit) my head on the wall when I fell down the stairs. - hit</p>\r\n<p>My father ___ (to become) angry when I quit school last year. - became</p>\r\n<p>My grandmother ___ (to wear) her dentures for her date with Mr. Olsen. - wore</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to lead) my horse to the stream for a drink of cold water. - led</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (to fly) the kite in the field all day. - flew</p>\r\n<p>The teacher ___ (to write) on the blackboard with pink chalk. - wrote</p>\r\n<p>Emy and Meghan ___ (to swim) with dolphins when they were on vacation in Florida. - swam</p>\r\n<p>The princess ___ (to weep) alone in her room. - wept</p>\r\n<p>She says that she ___ (to tell) the truth to the jury. - told</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to stand) on the corner in the rain and waited for you for twenty minutes. - stood</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (to give) me a housecoat and a puppy for my birthday. - gave</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:24:11', '2019-07-26 02:30:14'),
(133, 5, 20, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense: Negative Form', NULL, 'the-simple-past-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>did not</strong> after the subject and use the simple form of the verb to create the negative form of the simple past tense for regular and irregular verbs.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I did not break</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I did not break the cup.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you did not answer</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You did not answer me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he did not believe</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He did not believe you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she did not pass</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She did not pass her test.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it did not jump</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It did not jump on me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we did not sell</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We did not sell our house.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they did not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they did not touch</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They did not touch it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the simple past tense can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>didn\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I did not boil</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I didn\'t boil</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I didn\'t boil the eggs.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you did not build</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you didn\'t build</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You didn\'t build your house.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he did not want</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he didn\'t want</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He didn\'t want coffee.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she did not do</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she didn\'t do</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She didn\'t do her homework.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it did not cost</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it didn\'t cost</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It didn\'t cost a lot.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we did not sign</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we didn\'t sign</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We didn\'t sign it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they did not find</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they didn\'t find</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They didn\'t find their cat.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:31:01', '2019-07-26 02:53:05'),
(134, 5, 20, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to shave</p>\r\n<p>to waste</p>\r\n<p>to apologize</p>\r\n<p>to report</p>\r\n<p>bottle</p>\r\n<p>screen</p>\r\n<p>skin</p>\r\n<p>income</p>\r\n<p>medicine</p>\r\n<p>valuable</p>\r\n<p>mussels</p>\r\n<p>clam</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:53:45', '2019-07-26 02:54:55'),
(135, 5, 20, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form of the simple past tense.&nbsp; Write the sentence once using did not and once using didn\'t.</p>\r\n<p>They watched the hockey game on their new big screen TV.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I forgot to tell him.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>She wasted my valuable time.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>Marcia reported her income.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>I shook the bottle of medicine.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>My uncle shaved his head.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>He apologized to his friend.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>We found clams and mussels in the sand on the beach.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>The police read the man his rights.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>It scratched my skin.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:55:07', '2019-07-26 02:58:52'),
(136, 5, 20, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>Use your dictionary to find the meaning of the following verbs and vocabulary words needed for this exercise before you begin.&nbsp; Write the words in your language in the space provided.</p>\r\n<p>to translate</p>\r\n<p>to deposit</p>\r\n<p>to gain</p>\r\n<p>to last</p>\r\n<p>to prevent</p>\r\n<p>to express</p>\r\n<p>to brush</p>\r\n<p>to save</p>\r\n<p>inch</p>\r\n<p>wallet</p>\r\n<p>hat</p>\r\n<p>shower</p>\r\n<p>upstairs</p>\r\n<p>pay</p>\r\n<p>trip</p>\r\n<p>litter box</p>\r\n<p>Greece</p>\r\n<p>leftovers</p>\r\n<p>opinion</p>\r\n<p>mitten</p>\r\n<p>antenna</p>\r\n<p>pipe</p>\r\n<p>grandson</p>\r\n<p>granddaughter</p>\r\n<p>savings account</p>\r\n<p>pantyhose</p>\r\n<p>horoscope</p>\r\n<p>plumber</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 02:59:11', '2019-07-26 03:00:42'),
(137, 5, 20, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the negative form using the contraction <strong>didn\'t</strong> and the simple form of the verb.</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (prevented) the accident. - didn\'t prevent</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (expressed) her opinion. - didn\'t express</p>\r\n<p>The movie ___ (lasted) three hours. - didn\'t last</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (went) to see their granddaughter and grandson. - didn\'t go</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (saved) a lot of money for their trip to Greece. - didn\'t save</p>\r\n<p>Patricia ___ (lost) her mittens, scarf, and hat at school. - didn\'t lose</p>\r\n<p>Sonia ___ (translated) the letter. - didn\'t translate</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (bought) a gift for her. - didn\'t buy</p>\r\n<p>Mario ___ (found) a black leather wallet in the snow. - didn\'t find</p>\r\n<p>We ___ (put) the leftovers in plastic bags. - didn\'t put</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (tore) my pantyhose. - didn\'t tear</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (knew) you were there. - didn\'t know</p>\r\n<p>He ___ (deposited) his pay in his savings account. - didn\'t deposit</p>\r\n<p>The plumber ___ (fixed) the pipes, shower, and toilet in the bathroom upstairs. - didn\'t fix</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (cleaned) the litter box this morning. - didn\'t clean</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (read) my horoscope today. - didn\'t read</p>\r\n<p>The wind ___ (bent) the antenna. - didn\'t bend</p>\r\n<p>Laura ___ (grew) two inches last year. - didn\'t grow</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (gained) ten punds. - didn\'t gain.</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (brushed) the cat yesterday. - didn\'t brush</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 03:01:01', '2019-07-26 03:09:11'),
(138, 5, 21, 1, 'The Simple Past Tense: Question Form', NULL, 'the-simple-past-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place did before the subject to create questions in the simple past tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is always used when creating questions in the simple past tense with regular and irregular verbs.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>I ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did I eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did I eat your sandwich?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>you ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did you eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did you eat my last cookie?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>he ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did he eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did he eat his dessert?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>she ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did she eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did she eat the vegetables?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did it eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did it eat the egg?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>we ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did we eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did we eat everything?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>they ate</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>did they eat</td>\r\n<td>&rarr;</td>\r\n<td>Did they eat the meat?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 03:58:59', '2019-07-26 04:02:30'),
(139, 5, 21, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '<p>to weigh</p>\r\n<p>to elect</p>\r\n<p>to escape</p>\r\n<p>to change</p>\r\n<p>to cheat</p>\r\n<p>to offend</p>\r\n<p>to indicate</p>\r\n<p>to remain</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:03:02', '2019-07-26 04:03:31'),
(140, 5, 21, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the simple past tense by placing <strong>did</strong> before the subject and using the simple form of the verb.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p>You saw the beautiful rainbow. &rarr; Did you see the beautiful rainbow?</p>\r\n<p>He offended your when he said that. &rarr; Did he offend you when he said that?</p>\r\n<p>Exercises:</p>\r\n<p>Jessica found a starfish on the beach. - Did Jessica find a starfish on the beach?</p>\r\n<p>The squirrel ate the peanuts. - Did the squirrel eat the peanuts?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:03:49', '2019-07-26 04:07:10'),
(141, 5, 21, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '<p>to load</p>\r\n<p>to lock</p>\r\n<p>to pick</p>\r\n<p>to ask</p>\r\n<p>to appear</p>\r\n<p>to attend</p>\r\n<p>to convince</p>\r\n<p>to climb</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:07:28', '2019-07-26 04:07:51'),
(142, 5, 21, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following setences using <strong>did</strong> and the simple form of the verb to create questions in the simple past tense.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>You took a picture of the sunset. - Did you take a picture of the sunset?</p>\r\n<p>She locked the safe. - Did she lock the safe?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:07:58', '2019-07-26 04:09:41'),
(143, 5, 22, 1, 'Prepositions: In and On', NULL, 'prepositions--in-and-on', NULL, '<h3>Use <strong>in</strong> as a preposition to indicate:</h3>\r\n<p><strong>the position or location:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The towels are in the dryer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the year of the occurrence:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We married in 2003.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the months and seasons:</strong></p>\r\n<p>My flower garden is beautiful in the summer.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s my birthday in April.</p>\r\n<p><strong>points of the day (except for at night):</strong></p>\r\n<p>He left in the afternoon.</p>\r\n<p>He sleeps at night.</p>\r\n<p>He goes in the morning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>location within countries, cities, states, and provinces:</strong></p>\r\n<p>She goes to school in Montreal.</p>\r\n<p>He lives in Ohio.</p>\r\n<p>We had fun in Mexico.</p>\r\n<p>I met him in British Columbia.</p>\r\n<h3>Use on as a preposition to indicate:</h3>\r\n<p><strong>an object supported by a top surface:</strong></p>\r\n<p>the cup is on the table</p>\r\n<p><strong>the directional position of something:</strong></p>\r\n<p>It\'s the first door on the left.</p>\r\n<p><strong>a time of occurrence:</strong></p>\r\n<p>I worked on the weekend.</p>\r\n<p>She was sick on Friday.</p>\r\n<p><strong>a method of transportation (exception: in the car)</strong></p>\r\n<p>I felt sick on the plane.</p>\r\n<p>I felt sick in the car.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the mean of expression:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We talked on the phone for two hours.</p>\r\n<p>They played the song on the radio.</p>\r\n<p>I watched it on TV last week.</p>\r\n<p><strong>the subject of study:</strong></p>\r\n<p>I have a good book on horses.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:10:52', '2019-07-26 19:45:37'),
(144, 5, 22, 2, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences correctly by choosing <strong>in</strong> or <strong>on</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>The garbage can is (in, on) the garage. - in</p>\r\n<p>Do you see signs of life (in, on) the moon? - on</p>\r\n<p>We will talk about it (in, on) the morning. - in</p>\r\n<p>We spent five days (in, on) Paris. - in</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:19:10', '2019-07-26 04:20:51'),
(145, 5, 22, 3, 'Vocabulary 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-1', NULL, '<p>economy</p>\r\n<p>blister</p>\r\n<p>wart</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:21:06', '2019-07-26 04:21:17'),
(146, 5, 22, 4, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with in or on.</p>\r\n<p>They saw you [in, on] TV last night. - on</p>\r\n<p>My aunt died [in, on] August. - in</p>\r\n<p>She lives [in, on] the city. - in</p>\r\n<p>The people are [in, on] the ship. - on</p>\r\n<p>It\'s garbage day [in, on] Thursday. - on</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:21:24', '2019-07-26 04:23:01'),
(147, 5, 23, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Present Tense', NULL, 'there-is-and-there-are--present-tense', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>there is</strong> and <strong>there are</strong> to show that something exists.&nbsp; Use <strong>there is</strong> with singular nouns and <strong>there are</strong> with plural nouns.</p>\r\n<p>Singular</p>\r\n<p>There is a gift for you on the table</p>\r\n<p>There is a sand castle on the beach.</p>\r\n<p>There is a dove on the fence.</p>\r\n<p>There is a button on the floor.</p>\r\n<p>Plural</p>\r\n<p>There are two gifts for you on the table.</p>\r\n<p>There are a lot of sand castles on the beach.</p>\r\n<p>There are many doves on the fence.</p>\r\n<p>There are three buttons on the floor.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:23:30', '2019-07-26 04:26:20'),
(148, 5, 23, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:26:52', '2019-07-26 04:26:52'),
(149, 5, 23, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences by choosing <strong>there is</strong> or <strong>there are</strong> depending on whether the noun is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>[There is, There are] many meatballs and red peppers in the sauce. - There are</p>\r\n<p>[There is, There are] a whiteboard in my classroom. - There is</p>\r\n<p>[There is, There are] rocks in my boot. - There are</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:27:13', '2019-07-26 04:29:05'),
(150, 5, 23, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:29:21', '2019-07-26 04:29:21'),
(151, 5, 23, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> depending on whether the noun directly following the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] many stars in the sky. - are</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] a beehive in the garage. - is</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] enough proof. - is</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] a big roller coaster over there. - is</p>\r\n<p>There [is, are] two houses on this street. - are</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:29:31', '2019-07-26 04:31:46'),
(152, 5, 24, 1, 'Ther Is and There Are: Present Tense: Negative Form', NULL, 'ther-is-and-there-are--present-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place not after <strong>there is</strong> and <strong>there are</strong> to create a negative sentence.</p>\r\n<p>there is &rarr; there is not &rarr; There is not a rocking chair downstairs.</p>\r\n<p>there are &rarr; there are not &rarr; There are not many blankets on my bed.</p>\r\n<p>The negative form of <strong>there is</strong> and <strong>there are</strong> can also be expressed with the contractions <strong>there isn\'t</strong> and <strong>there aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>there is not &rarr; there isn\'t &rarr; There isn\'t a bug in the house.</p>\r\n<p>there are not &rarr; there aren\'t &rarr; There aren\'t many leftovers.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:32:22', '2019-07-26 04:35:50'),
(153, 5, 24, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:36:09', '2019-07-26 04:36:09'),
(154, 5, 24, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to express the negative form of there is and there are.&nbsp; Write the sentence once using <strong>is not</strong> and <strong>are not</strong> and once using the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>There is a lot of shade in the backyard.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>There are two yellow folders on my desk.</p>\r\n<p>___</p>\r\n<p>___</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:36:17', '2019-07-26 04:38:39'),
(155, 5, 24, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:38:57', '2019-07-26 04:38:57'),
(156, 5, 24, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Use the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong> to complete the following negative sentences.</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] enough time. - isn\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] a pay phone in my school. - isn\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] two seats available for us. - aren\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [isn\'t, aren\'t] many people here. - aren\'t</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:39:05', '2019-07-26 04:41:34'),
(157, 5, 25, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Present Tense: Question Form', NULL, 'there-is-and-there-are--present-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> before <strong>there</strong> to create questions in the present tense.</p>\r\n<p>there is &rarr; is there &rarr; Is there a kitten outside?</p>\r\n<p>there are &rarr; are there &rarr; Are there ducks in the pond?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:42:01', '2019-07-26 04:43:36'),
(158, 5, 25, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:43:48', '2019-07-26 04:43:48'),
(159, 5, 25, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions by placing <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> before <strong>there</strong>.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>There is a vending machine in the cafeteria. - Is there a vending machine in the cafetieria?</p>\r\n<p>There are enough life jackets in the boat. - Are there enough life jackets in the boat?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:44:35', '2019-07-26 04:46:25'),
(160, 5, 25, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:46:38', '2019-07-26 04:46:38'),
(161, 5, 25, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following questions with <strong>is</strong> or <strong>are</strong> depending on whether the noun directly referring to the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>[is, are] there fingerprints on the gun? - are</p>\r\n<p>[is, are] there a pool table in the playroom? - is</p>\r\n<p>[is, are] there porcupines in the yard? - are</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:46:45', '2019-07-26 04:48:35'),
(162, 5, 26, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Past Tense', NULL, 'there-is-and-there-are--past-tense', NULL, '<p>The past tense of the singular <strong>there is</strong> is <strong>there was</strong> and the past tense of the plural <strong>there are</strong> is <strong>there were</strong>.&nbsp; Use <strong>there was</strong> and <strong>there were</strong> to show that something existed in the past.</p>\r\n<p>there is &rarr; there was &rarr; There was a loud noise downstairs last night.</p>\r\n<p>there are &rarr; there were &rarr; There were dark clouds in the sky.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:49:02', '2019-07-26 04:51:39'),
(163, 5, 26, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:52:00', '2019-07-26 04:52:00'),
(164, 5, 26, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following past tense sentences by choosing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> depending on whether the noun directly following the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] rust on the knife. - was</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] rules to follow. - were</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a big sale at the mall, so I bought a scarf and shoes. - was</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a CD player in my car but someone stole it. - was</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:52:09', '2019-07-26 04:54:08'),
(165, 5, 26, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:54:28', '2019-07-26 04:54:28'),
(166, 5, 26, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following past tense sentences using <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> depending on whether the noun directly following the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a new priest in my church today. - was</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a lot of clothespins in the bag. - were</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] many houses for sale last year. - were</p>\r\n<p>There [was, were] a rainbow after the storm. - was</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:54:53', '2019-07-26 04:56:47'),
(167, 5, 27, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Past Tense: Negative Form', NULL, 'there-is-and-there-are--past-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after <strong>there was</strong> and <strong>there were</strong> to create a negative sentence.</p>\r\n<p>there was &rarr; there was not &rarr; There was not a doll on the chair.</p>\r\n<p>there were &rarr; there were not &rarr; There were not many kids in the pool.</p>\r\n<p>The negative form of <strong>there was</strong> and <strong>there were</strong> can also be expressed with the contractions <strong>there wasn\'t</strong> and <strong>there weren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>there was not &rarr; there wasn\'t &rarr; There wasn\'t a bruise on his arm.</p>\r\n<p>there were not &rarr; there weren\'t &rarr; There weren\'t many fish in the lake.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 04:59:10', '2019-07-26 05:02:28');
