(171, 5, 27, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Use the contractions <strong>wasn\'t</strong> or <strong>weren\'t</strong> to complete the following negative sentences.</p>\r\n<p>There [wasn\'t, weren\'t] a bottle of mouthwash on the shelf in the bathroom. - wasn\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [wasn\'t, weren\'t] many chapters in the book. - weren\'t</p>\r\n<p>There [wasn\'t, weren\'t] a rope in the boat. - wasn\'t</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 05:05:47', '2019-07-26 05:07:19'),
(172, 5, 28, 1, 'There Is and There Are: Past Tense: Question Form', NULL, 'there-is-and-there-are--past-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before <strong>there</strong> to create questions in the past tense.</p>\r\n<p>there was &rarr; was there &rarr; Was there a cushion on the chair?</p>\r\n<p>there were &rarr; were there &rarr; Were there enough snacks for the kids?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 06:59:30', '2019-07-26 07:00:57'),
(173, 5, 28, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:01:14', '2019-07-26 07:01:14'),
(174, 5, 28, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions by placing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before <strong>there</strong>.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>There were many knights to guard the castle in the kingdom. - Were there many knights...?</p>\r\n<p>There was a wooden outhouse behind our cottage in the country. - Was there a wooden outhouse...?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:01:23', '2019-07-26 07:03:17'),
(175, 5, 28, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:03:36', '2019-07-26 07:03:36'),
(176, 5, 28, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following past tense questions with <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> depending on whether the noun directly referring to the verb is singular or plural.</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there dinosaurs on Earth? - were</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there a cardboard box in the bedroom? - was</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there a lock on the door? - was</p>\r\n<p>[Was, Were] there many pennies in the jar? - were</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:03:44', '2019-07-26 07:05:46'),
(177, 5, 29, 1, 'Prepositions: To and At', NULL, 'prepositions--to-and-at', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>to</strong> as a preposition to describe a movement or an action toward a person, place, or thing.</p>\r\n<p>I walk to school.</p>\r\n<p>She goes to the bank every week.</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>at</strong> as a preposition to describe an action performed when a person or thing arrives at a location.</p>\r\n<p>We learn a lot at school.</p>\r\n<p>I hurt my knee at the playground.</p>\r\n<p>Use at as a preposition to refer to time.</p>\r\n<p>We have a meeting at three o\'clock.</p>\r\n<p>He eats breakfast at 7:30 A.M.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:06:12', '2019-07-26 07:08:39'),
(178, 5, 29, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:08:56', '2019-07-26 07:08:56'),
(179, 5, 29, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences correctly by choosing <strong>to</strong> or <strong>at</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Please explain [to, at] me. - to</p>\r\n<p>The girls ate cake [to, at] the birthday party. - at</p>\r\n<p>We saw Tony and his brother [to, at] the restaurant. - at</p>', 1, 40, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:09:04', '2019-07-26 19:30:25'),
(180, 5, 29, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:10:39', '2019-07-26 07:10:39'),
(181, 5, 29, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>to</strong> or <strong>at</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>I forgot my homework [to, at] my house. - at</p>\r\n<p>They signed the contract [to, at] the courthouse. - at</p>\r\n<p>He sent a gift certificate [to, at] his mother. - to</p>\r\n<p>Throw it [to, at] me. - to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 07:10:52', '2019-07-26 07:12:16'),
(256, 5, 45, 1, 'The Present Perfect Tense', NULL, 'the-present-perfect-tense', NULL, '<p>The present perfect tense is used when the time of a past activity is not important or is not known in the sentence.&nbsp; Use <strong>has</strong> or <strong>have</strong> and the past participle of the verb with both regular and irregular verbs to form the present perfect tense.</p>\r\n<p>Contactions can also be used with the pronouns to create the present perfect tense.</p>\r\n<p>Regular</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PRESENT</td>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td >PRESENT PREFECT</td>\r\n<td >CONTRACTION</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I work</td>\r\n<td >I worked</td>\r\n<td >I have worked</td>\r\n<td >I\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you work</td>\r\n<td >you worked</td>\r\n<td >you have worked</td>\r\n<td >you\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he works</td>\r\n<td >he worked</td>\r\n<td >he has worked</td>\r\n<td >he\'s worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she works</td>\r\n<td >she worked</td>\r\n<td >she has worked</td>\r\n<td >she\'s worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it works</td>\r\n<td >it worked</td>\r\n<td >it has worked</td>\r\n<td >it\'s worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we work</td>\r\n<td >we worked</td>\r\n<td >we have worked</td>\r\n<td >we\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they work</td>\r\n<td >they worked</td>\r\n<td >they have worked</td>\r\n<td >they\'ve worked</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Irregular</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PRESENT</td>\r\n<td >SIMPLE PAST</td>\r\n<td >PRESENT PERFECT</td>\r\n<td >CONTRACTION</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I take</td>\r\n<td >I took</td>\r\n<td >I have taken</td>\r\n<td >I\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you take</td>\r\n<td >you took</td>\r\n<td >you have taken</td>\r\n<td >you\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he takes</td>\r\n<td >he took</td>\r\n<td >he has taken</td>\r\n<td >he\'s taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she takes</td>\r\n<td >she took</td>\r\n<td >she has taken</td>\r\n<td >she\'s taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it takes</td>\r\n<td >it took</td>\r\n<td >it has taken</td>\r\n<td >it\'s taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we take</td>\r\n<td >we took</td>\r\n<td >we have taken</td>\r\n<td >we\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they take</td>\r\n<td >they took</td>\r\n<td >they have taken</td>\r\n<td >they\'ve taken</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-29 02:53:24', '2019-07-29 03:00:52'),
(182, 5, 30, 1, 'The Present Progressing (Continuous) Tense', NULL, 'the-present-progressing--continuous--tense', NULL, '<p>The present progressive is used to describe an activity that is presently in progress.&nbsp; It is formed using the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and by adding <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am drinking my milk with a straw.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you are drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You are drinking my wine.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he drinks</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he is drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He is drinking a cold beer.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she drinks</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she is drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She is drinking a cup of tea.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it drinks</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it is drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It is drinking the water in the toilet.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we are drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We are drinking orange juice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they drink</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they are drinking</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They are drinking grape juice.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:51:49', '2019-07-26 21:55:56'),
(183, 5, 30, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:56:14', '2019-07-26 21:56:14'),
(184, 5, 30, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences in the present progressive tense.&nbsp; Use the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong>, and add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>The wolf (to howl) at the moon. - is howling</p>\r\n<p>Sheila (to worry) now because her daughter is late. - is worrying</p>\r\n<p>It is cold and we (to shiver). - are shivering</p>\r\n<p>They (to cross) the lake in a canoe. - are crossing</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:56:29', '2019-07-26 21:59:01'),
(185, 5, 30, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:59:27', '2019-07-26 21:59:27'),
(186, 5, 30, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences to form the present progressive tense.&nbsp; Use the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and add <strong>-ing</strong> to the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>She ___ (to dress) the baby in the bedroom. - is dressing</p>\r\n<p>You ___ (to cough) a lot. - are coughing</p>\r\n<p>They ___ (to sit) in the dining room. - are sitting</p>\r\n<p>I ___ (to leave) now. - am leaving</p>\r\n<p>Bob ___ (to send) a postcard. - is sending</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 21:59:36', '2019-07-26 22:03:03'),
(187, 5, 31, 1, 'The Present Progressive (Continuous) Tense: Negative Form', NULL, 'the-present-progressive--continuous--tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place not after the verb To Be to create the negative form of the present progressive tense.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not following you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you are not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You are not following him.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he is not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He is not following a recipe.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she is not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She is not following the rules.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it is not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It is not following me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we are not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We are not following the car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they are not following</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They are not following us.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the present progressive tense can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.&nbsp; There is no contraction for <strong>am not</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not washing the floor.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you aren\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You aren\'t washing your hair.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he isn\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He isn\'t washing his hands.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she isn\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She isn\'t washing the dishes.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it isn\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It isn\'t washing its baby.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we aren\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We aren\'t washing our car.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are not washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they aren\'t washing</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They aren\'t washing the dog.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:03:55', '2019-07-26 22:10:48'),
