(209, 5, 35, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the past progressive tense by placing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>The police were stopping everyone at the corner. - Were the police stopping?</p>\r\n<p>My rubber duck was floating in the bath. - Was my rubber duck floating?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:50:12', '2019-07-26 22:52:07'),
(210, 5, 35, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:52:16', '2019-07-26 22:52:16'),
(211, 5, 35, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the past progressive tense by placing <strong>was</strong> or <strong>were</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>She was starting her car. - Was she starting her car?</p>\r\n<p>They were begging us to stay for supper. - Were they begging us?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-26 22:52:29', '2019-07-26 22:54:15'),
(212, 5, 36, 1, 'Prepositions: From and Of', NULL, 'prepositions--from-and-of', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>from</strong> as a preposition to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate a starting point of a movement</strong></p>\r\n<p>We drove from Montreal to Toronto.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate a starting point of an action</strong></p>\r\n<p>My husband called me from work.</p>\r\n<p><strong>measure between points</strong></p>\r\n<p>I work from 8:00 A.M. to 4:00 P.M.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate the source</strong></p>\r\n<p>She got the information from John.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>of</strong> as a preposition to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate the cause or reason of an action</strong></p>\r\n<p>He died of a heart attack.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate belonging</strong></p>\r\n<p>I met the queen of England.</p>\r\n<p><strong>indicate the contents</strong></p>\r\n<p>I drank two cups of coffee this morning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>describe a characteristic of a person</strong></p>\r\n<p>He is a man of great courage.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:01:45', '2019-07-27 04:07:09'),
(213, 5, 36, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:07:33', '2019-07-27 04:07:33'),
(214, 5, 36, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences correctly by choosing <strong>from</strong> or <strong>at</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>We gave her a bouquet [from, of] flowers. - of</p>\r\n<p>I got a toothbrush [from, of] my dentist. - from</p>\r\n<p>He is a member [from, of] the hockey team. - of</p>\r\n<p>She sent me a postcard [from, of] Canada. - from</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:07:41', '2019-07-27 04:09:43'),
(215, 5, 36, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:10:05', '2019-07-27 04:10:05'),
(216, 5, 36, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>from</strong> or <strong>of</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>She bought a basket [from, of] fruit for us. - of</p>\r\n<p>He is a man [from, of] experience. - of</p>\r\n<p>Are you [from, of] Montreal? - from</p>\r\n<p>The odor is coming [from, of] the refrigerator. - from</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:10:16', '2019-07-27 04:11:46'),
(217, 5, 37, 1, 'Will: Future Tense', NULL, 'will--future-tense', NULL, '<p>Use <strong>will</strong> to create the future tense for all persons.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb always follows <strong>will</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will hold your books.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You will hold the baby.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He will hold my hand.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She will hold her doll.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It will hold the ball.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We will hold our fishing rods.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they will hold</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They will hold the ladder.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:12:14', '2019-07-27 04:15:05'),
(218, 5, 37, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:15:30', '2019-07-27 04:15:30'),
(219, 5, 37, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', 'Rewrite the following sentences in the future tense by using will and the simple form of the verb in parentheses.', '<p>I (to climb) to the top of the lighthouse to see the ships. - will climb</p>\r\n<p>You (to become) a rich and famous author. - will become</p>\r\n<p>The government (to reduce) taxes next year. - will reduce</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:16:09', '2019-07-27 04:17:22'),
(220, 5, 37, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:17:36', '2019-07-27 04:17:36'),
(221, 5, 37, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', 'Complete the sentences using will and the simple form of the verb in parentheses to create the future tense.', '<p>Brian (to calculate) his pay. - Brian will calculate his pay.</p>\r\n<p>We (to balance) our budget. - We will balance our budget.</p>\r\n<p>I (to miss) you. - I will miss you.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:18:20', '2019-07-27 04:20:02'),
(222, 5, 38, 1, 'Will: Future Tense: Negative Form', NULL, 'will--future-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>not</strong> after <strong>will</strong> to create the negative form of the future tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb always follows <strong>will not</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I will not be there.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You will not say that.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He will not pay me.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She will not see you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It will not eat.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We will not borrow money.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You will not drive to New York.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the future tense with <strong>will</strong> can be expressed with the contraction <strong>won\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I won\'t go.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You won\'t convince her.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He won\'t know.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She won\'t sleep late.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It won\'t bite you.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We won\'t spend a lot.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will not</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they won\'t</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They won\'t help us.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:20:35', '2019-07-27 04:26:08'),
(223, 5, 38, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:26:36', '2019-07-27 04:26:36'),
(224, 5, 38, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the negative form of the future tense.&nbsp; Write your answer once with <strong>will not</strong> and once with the contraction <strong>won\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>He will declare bankruptcy. - He will not declare bankruptcy.</p>\r\n<p>He will declare bankruptcy. - He won\'t declare bankruptcy.</p>\r\n<p>The man will confess to the murder. - The man will not confess to the murder.</p>\r\n<p>The man will confess to the murder. - The man won\'t confess to the murder.</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:26:45', '2019-07-27 04:29:02'),
(225, 5, 38, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:29:11', '2019-07-27 04:29:11'),
(226, 5, 38, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences by using the contraction <strong>won\'t</strong> and the simple form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n<p>You ___ (to ruin) your reputation. - won\'t ruin</p>\r\n<p>It ___ (to clog) the drain. - won\'t clog</p>\r\n<p>My company ___ (to issue) the newsletter. - won\'t issue</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:29:18', '2019-07-27 04:30:55'),
(227, 5, 39, 1, 'Will: Future Tense: Question Form', NULL, 'will--future-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place <strong>will</strong> before the subject to create questions in the future tense.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is always used when forming questions with <strong>will</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will I like</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will I like it?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will you call</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will you call me?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will he write</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will he write a book?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will she join</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will she join us for dinner?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will it annoy</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will it annoy you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will we need</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will we need a new car?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they will</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >will they worry</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Will they worry about me?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:31:20', '2019-07-27 04:34:05'),
(228, 5, 39, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:34:17', '2019-07-27 04:34:17'),
(229, 5, 39, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the future tense by placing <strong>will</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>The snow will disappear in the spring. - Will the snow disappear in the spring?</p>\r\n<p>Your mother will punish you for that. - Will your mother punish you for that?</p>\r\n<p>The police will accuse Sara. - Will the police accuse Sara?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:34:29', '2019-07-27 04:36:32'),
(230, 5, 39, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:39:44', '2019-07-27 04:39:44'),
(231, 5, 39, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the future tense by placing <strong>will</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>It will arrive on time. - Will it arrive on time?</p>\r\n<p>He will publish his report. - Will he publish his report?</p>', 1, 30, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 04:40:02', '2019-07-27 04:42:15'),
(232, 2, 1, 3, 'Vocabulario Nuevo 2 - Converted', NULL, 'vocabulario-nuevo-2', NULL, '<p>prisa o urgencia con que se hace algo - premura</p>\r\n<p>ruidoso, turbulento - estrepitoso</p>\r\n<p>descarga de datos - volcado</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;tesoro de piratas - bot&iacute;n</p>\r\n<p>olor - hedor</p>\r\n<p>serie numerosa de golpes dados a una persona como castigo o con la intenci&oacute;n de hacerle da&ntilde;o. - paliza</p>\r\n<p>tina; tina de manteca - tarrina</p>\r\n<p>Dejar a una persona o un animal moment&aacute;neamente sin capacidad para actuar o comportarse de forma coordinada y normal - aturdido</p>\r\n<p>derrotar, batir crema, envolver, dar con un l&aacute;tigo - azotar</p>\r\n<p>marcar un n&uacute;mero en el aparato telef&oacute;nico - disque</p>\r\n<p>cerdo macho.&nbsp; Persona que es vulgar, porfiado y necio - verraco</p>\r\n<p>dicho o hecho tonto [estupidez, tonter&iacute;a, pendejada, bobada, ridiculez] - bobada</p>\r\n<p>in between; involucrado; en el medio - de por medio</p>\r\n<p>agotado, muy cansado - fundido</p>\r\n<p>(lo que fuera) menester - necesario</p>\r\n<p>necesidad de una cosa - menester</p>\r\n<p>no es para menos - es logico</p>\r\n<p>lo de menos - the least importante</p>\r\n<p>algo que no va - inadaptados</p>\r\n<p>atribuir algo, una falta o culpa a alguien - achacar</p>\r\n<p>impaciencia, ansia, deseo, anhelo - af&aacute;n</p>\r\n<p>firme; convincente - contundente</p>\r\n<p>grueso, denso, tupido, gordo, cerrado - espeso</p>\r\n<p>agitar, sacudir, temblar, mover, menear - estremecer</p>\r\n<p>estrecho, reducido, peque&ntilde;o, restringido, corto - angosto</p>\r\n<p>plano, fluido, tranquilo, llano, blando - liso</p>\r\n<p>ben&eacute;volo, cari&ntilde;oso, benigno, favorable - bondadoso</p>\r\n<p>destruir, matar o causar da&ntilde;o de forma instant&aacute;nea - fulminar</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 18:33:09', '2020-04-30 05:08:26'),
(234, 2, 1, 4, 'Vocabulario Nuevo 3 - Converted', NULL, 'vocabulario-nuevo-3', NULL, '<p>donde fluyo de sangre - torrente sangu&iacute;neo</p>\r\n<p>Lookup - apa&ntilde;arse</p>\r\n<p>casualidad (Casualidades de guerra) - baja</p>\r\n<p>pago para ayudar o aportar - subvenci&oacute;n</p>\r\n<p>moderar o suavizar - ablandar</p>\r\n<p>crueldad, atrocidad - vicisitud</p>\r\n<p>compartir las mismas ideas, sentimientos, opiniones - comulgar</p>\r\n<p>no se preocupe - no se afane</p>\r\n<p>intimidar, espantar - amedrentar</p>\r\n<p>corresponder a alguien (vamos al asunto que nos ___) - competerse</p>\r\n<p>deseo vehemente en alguien, generalmente de forma impulsiva - antojar</p>\r\n<p>es algo nuevo?&nbsp; es una ___ - novedad</p>\r\n<p>acosar con insistencia, persiguiendo, molestando, golpeando, dando l&aacute;tigo - hostigar</p>\r\n<p>cultivado, bien educado - culto</p>\r\n<p>cort&eacute;s (polite) - educado</p>\r\n<p>aceptar y cumplir una orden, ley, o regla - acatar</p>\r\n<p>revuelta o agitaci&oacute;n con la que un grupo de personas quiere mostrar su oposici&oacute;n con violencia - mot&iacute;n</p>\r\n<p>acostarse, echarse - tumbarse</p>\r\n<p>re&ntilde;ir a una persona o expresi&oacute;n de forma autoritaria a causa de su actuaci&oacute;n o su comportamiento - reprender</p>\r\n<p>animar o apoyar a una persona por lo que hace, especialmente con expresiones y gritos. - jalear</p>\r\n<p>ambos direcciones - ambos sentidos</p>\r\n<p>held accountable - rendir&aacute;n cuentas</p>\r\n<p>puesto de bebidas y comidas sencillas al aire libre, especialmente en la playa. - chiringuito</p>\r\n<p>choza, barraca o cobertizo que se construye durante las fiestas populares para vender comidas y bebidas. - chinamo</p>\r\n<p>cortar, picar, talar, desmenuzar, partir - tajar</p>\r\n<p>u&ntilde;a y carne - carne y hueso</p>\r\n<p>wield, usar, ejercer, empunar, emplear - esgrimir</p>\r\n<p>tomar una cosa por la manija, especialmente un arma. - empu&ntilde;ar</p>\r\n<p>calmante, dulce, analg&eacute;sico (soothing) - tranquilizador</p>\r\n<p>habilidad, experiencia, maestr&iacute;a, oficio - destreza</p>\r\n<p>a medida que avanzas (____ avanza en el programma) - conforme</p>', 1, 42, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:03:51', '2020-04-30 05:08:30'),
