(239, 5, 40, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the sentences using the correct form of the verb <strong>To Be</strong> and the simple form of the verb in parenthese to create the future tense with <strong>be going to</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ going to ___ (to assume) that he is innocent. - are</p>\r\n<p>He ___ going to ___ (to suggest) something better at the meeting. - is</p>\r\n<p>I ___ going to ___ (to give) you a sample. - am</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:24:18', '2019-07-27 20:26:33');
