(240, 5, 41, 1, 'Be Going To: Future Tense: Negative Form', NULL, 'be-going-to--future-tense--negative-form', NULL, '<p>Place not after the verb <strong>To Be</strong> to create the negative form of the future tense with <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb always follows the negative form of <strong>be going to</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not going to lose.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >You are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You are not going to win.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >He is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He is not going to be there.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >She is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She is not going to eat it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >It is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It is not going to run.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >We are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We are not going to leave.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >They are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They are not going to talk.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>The negative form of the future tense with <strong>be going to</strong> can also be expressed with the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.&nbsp; There is no contraction for <strong>am not</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >I am not going to drive.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >you aren\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >You aren\'t going to forget.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >he isn\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >He isn\'t going to play.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >she isn\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >She isn\'t going to study.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >it isn\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >It isn\'t going to rain.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >we aren\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >We aren\'t going to try it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are not going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >they aren\'t going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >They aren\'t going to like it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:27:06', '2019-07-27 20:34:15'),
(241, 5, 41, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:34:31', '2019-07-27 20:34:31'),
(242, 5, 41, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the negative form of the future tense using <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; Write your answer once with <strong>am not</strong>, <strong>is not</strong>, and <strong>are not</strong> and once with <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>My company is going to annouce cutbacks for the new year. - is not going to</p>\r\n<p>My company is going to annouce cutbacks for the new year. - isn\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>We are going to submit the report in the morning. - are not going to</p>\r\n<p>We are going to submit the report in the morning. - aren\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>I am going to withdraw all of my money. - am not going to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:34:37', '2019-07-27 20:37:28'),
(243, 5, 41, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:37:40', '2019-07-27 20:37:40'),
(244, 5, 41, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences using <strong>am not</strong> or the contraction <strong>isn\'t</strong> or <strong>aren\'t</strong> to create the negative form of the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>We ___ going to trick you again. - aren\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>She ___ going to circle the right answer. - isn\'t going to</p>\r\n<p>I ___ going to label all the items in the store. - am not going to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:37:46', '2019-07-27 20:39:52'),
(245, 5, 42, 1, 'Be Going To: Future Tense: Question Form', NULL, 'be-going-to--future-tense--question-form', NULL, '<p>Place the verb to be before the subject to create questions in the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp; The simple form of the verb is always used when forming questions with <strong>be going to</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table class=\"table table-borderless\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >I am going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >am I going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Am I going to see you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >you are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are you going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are you going to visit me?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >he is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is he going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is he going to believe you?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >she is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is she going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is she going to be here?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >it is going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >is it going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Is it going to start soon?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >we are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are we going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are we going to agree?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >they are going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >are they going to</td>\r\n<td >&rarr;</td>\r\n<td >Are they going to park there?</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:40:31', '2019-07-27 20:43:43'),
(246, 5, 42, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:43:50', '2019-07-27 20:43:50'),
(247, 5, 42, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create the question form of the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong> by placing the verb <strong>to be</strong> before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>He is going to share this knowledge with the world. - is he going to</p>\r\n<p>You are going to provide me with a good explanantion. - are you going to</p>\r\n<p>I am going to drain the vegetables with this. - Am I going to</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:43:56', '2019-07-27 20:46:15'),
(248, 5, 42, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:46:27', '2019-07-27 20:46:27'),
(249, 5, 42, 5, 'Exercise 2', NULL, 'exercise-2', NULL, '<p>Rewrite the following sentences to create questions in the future tense of <strong>be going to</strong> by placing the verb to be before the subject.&nbsp; Don\'t forget to include a question mark (?) in your answer.</p>\r\n<p>He is going to promise to be good. - Is he going to promise to be good?</p>\r\n<p>You are going to wish for a car again. - Are you going to wish for a car again?</p>\r\n<p>I am going to compete with you. - Am I going to compete with you?</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:46:33', '2019-07-27 20:48:39'),
(250, 5, 43, 1, 'The Indefinite Articles: A and An', NULL, 'the-indefinite-articles--a-and-an', NULL, '<p>The indefinite articles <strong>a</strong> and <strong>an</strong> are used with singular nouns.&nbsp; Use <strong>a</strong> before most nouns or adjectives that begin with a consonant.&nbsp; Use <strong>an</strong> before most nouns or adjectives that begin with a vowel.</p>\r\n<p>a cup</p>\r\n<p>an empty cup</p>\r\n<p>a ball</p>\r\n<p>an orange ball</p>\r\n<p>a class</p>\r\n<p>an English class</p>\r\n<p>a bug</p>\r\n<p>an ugly bug</p>\r\n<p>an egg</p>\r\n<p>a brown egg</p>\r\n<p>an idea</p>\r\n<p>a good idea</p>\r\n<p>an owl</p>\r\n<p>a white own</p>\r\n<p>an accident</p>\r\n<p>a bad accident</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>a</strong> before nouns or adjectives that begin with a pronounced <strong>h</strong>, but use <strong>an</strong> before nouns or adjectives when the <strong>h</strong> is not pronounced.</p>\r\n<p>a house</p>\r\n<p>an honor</p>\r\n<p>a horse</p>\r\n<p>an hour</p>\r\n<p>a hammer</p>\r\n<p>an heir</p>\r\n<p>a hurricane</p>\r\n<p>an honest mistake</p>\r\n<p>Use <strong>a</strong> before nouns or adjectives if the vowel is pronounced as a consonant.&nbsp; The following words are pronounced with a <strong>y</strong> sound.</p>\r\n<p>a union</p>\r\n<p>a university</p>\r\n<p>a uniform</p>\r\n<p>a utensil</p>\r\n<p>The following words are pronounced with the <strong>w</strong> sound.</p>\r\n<p>a one-hour class</p>\r\n<p>a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:49:13', '2019-07-27 20:55:49'),
(251, 5, 43, 2, 'Vocabulary List 1', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-1', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:56:13', '2019-07-27 20:56:13'),
(252, 5, 43, 3, 'Exercise 1', NULL, 'exercise-1', NULL, '<p>Complete the following sentences with <strong>a</strong> or <strong>an</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>I ate ___ orange, ___ banana, and ___ peach today. - an, a, a</p>\r\n<p>There is ___ wild ostrich in the field. - a</p>\r\n<p>I want to live on ___ island for ___ month.</p>\r\n<p>There is ___ spider, ___ ant, and ___ fly in the kitchen. - a, an, a</p>', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:56:21', '2019-07-27 20:58:25'),
(253, 5, 43, 4, 'Vocabulary List 2', NULL, 'vocabulary-list-2', NULL, '', 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2019-07-27 20:58:35', '2019-07-27 20:59:26'),
